{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov/geographies/reference-files/time-series/geo/gazetteer-files.html|publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]]|accessdate=2011-04-23|date=2011-02-12|title=US Gazetteer files: 2010, 2000, and 1990}}</ref>\n\nAccording to the [[United States Census Bureau]], the town has a total area of {{convert|0.51|sqmi|sqkm|2}}, all of it land.<ref name=\"Gazetteer files\">{{cite web|title=US Gazetteer files 2010 |url=https://www.census.gov/geo/www/gazetteer/files/Gaz_places_national.txt |publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]] |accessdate=2012-12-14 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120125061959/http://www.census.gov/geo/www/gazetteer/files/Gaz_places_national.txt |archivedate=2012-01-25 }}</ref>\n\n==Demographics==\n{{US Census population\n|1920= 200\n|1930= 192\n|1940= 221\n|1950= 206\n|1960= 199\n|1970= 146\n|1980= 433\n|1990= 272\n|2000= 348\n|2010= 440\n|estyear=2018\n|estimate=418\n|estref=<ref name=\"USCensusEst2018CenPopScriptOnlyDirtyFixDoNotUse\">{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov/programs-surveys/popest/data/tables.2018.html|title=Population and Housing Unit Estimates|accessdate=June 4, 2019}}</ref>\n|footnote=U.S. Decennial Census<ref name=\"DecennialCensus\">{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov/programs-surveys/decennial-census.html|title=Census of Population and Housing|publisher=Census.gov|accessdate=June 4, 2015}}</ref>\n}}\n\n===2010 census===\nAs of the [[census]]<ref name =\"wwwcensusgov\">{{cite web|title=U.S. Census website|url=https://www.census.gov|publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]]|accessdate=2012-12-14}}</ref> of 2010, there were 440 people, 183 households, and 114 families living in the town. The [[population density]] was {{convert|862.7|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|1}}. There were 223 housing units at an average density of {{convert|437.3|/sqmi|/km2|1}}. The ethnic makeup of the town was 94.1% [[Caucasian (U.S. Census)|White]], 0.5% [[Native American (U.S. Census)|Native American]], 0.2% [[Asian (U.S. Census)|Asian]], 4.8% from [[Race (U.S. Census)|other races]], and 0.5% from two or more ethnic groups. [[Hispanic (U.S. Census)|Hispanic]] or [[Latino (U.S. Census)|Latino]] of any ethnic groups were 11.4% of the population.\n\nThere were 183 households of which 34.4% had children under the age of 18 living with them, 49.7% were [[Marriage|married couples]] living together, 7.7% had a female householder with no husband present, 4.9% had a male householder with no wife present, and 37.7% were non-families. 30.1% of all households were made up of individuals and 7.7% had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older. The average household size was 2.40 and the average family size was 3.01.\n\nThe median age in the town was 34.3 years. 27% of residents were under the age of 18; 8.5% were between the ages of 18 and 24; 25.9% were from 25 to 44; 28.2% were from 45 to 64; and 10.5% were 65 years of age or older. The gender makeup of the town was 52.7% male and 47.3% female.\n\n===2000 census===\nAs of the [[census]]<ref name=\"GR2\" /> of 2000, there were 348 people, 147 households, and 88 families living in the town. The [[population density]] was 705.8 people per square mile (274.2/km\u00b2). There were 197 housing units at an average density of 399.6 per square mile (155.2/km\u00b2). The racial makeup of the town was 94.83% [[White (U.S. Census)|White]], 2.59% [[Native American (U.S. Census)|Native American]], 0.29% [[Asian (U.S. Census)|Asian]], 1.72% from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 0.57% from two or more races. [[Hispanic (U.S. Census)|Hispanic]] or [[Latino (U.S. Census)|Latino]] of any race were 5.17% of the population.\n\nThere were 147 households out of which 32.0% had children under the age of 18 living with them, 44.9% were [[Marriage|married couples]] living together, 9.5% had a female householder with no husband present, and 40.1% were non-families. 29.3% of all households were made up of individuals and 10.9% had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older. The average household size was 2.37 and the average family size was 2.97.\n\nIn the town, the population was spread out with 26.1% under the age of 18, 6.3% from 18 to 24, 31.0% from 25 to 44, 25.6% from 45 to 64, and 10.9% who were 65 years of age or older. The median age was 39 years. For every 100 females, there were 112.2 males. For every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 100.8 males.\n\nThe median income for a household in the town was $29,688, and the median income for a family was $38,250. Males had a median income of $32,031 versus $21,250 for females. The [[per capita income]] for the town was $20,812. About 7.9% of families and 14.9% of the population were below the [[poverty line]], including 8.4% of those under age 18 and 10.8% of those age 65 or over.\n\n==Climate==\nThis [[climate|climatic]] region is typified by large seasonal temperature differences, with warm to hot (and often humid) summers and cold (sometimes severely cold) winters.  According to the [[K\u00f6ppen Climate Classification]] system, Baggs has a [[humid continental climate]], abbreviated \"Dfb\" on climate maps.<ref>[http://www.weatherbase.com/weather/weather-summary.php3?s=484084&cityname=Baggs%2C+Wyoming%2C+United+States+of+America&units= Climate Summary for Baggs, Wyoming]</ref>\n{{Weather box\n|location = Baggs, Wyoming\n|single line = Yes\n|metric first = Yes\n|Jan high F = 32\n|Feb high F = 36\n|Mar high F = 47\n|Apr high F = 58\n|May high F = 68\n|Jun high F = 79\n|Jul high F = 86\n|Aug high F = 83\n|Sep high F = 74\n|Oct high F = 60\n|Nov high F = 43\n|Dec high F = 33\n|year high F = 58\n|Jan low F = 5\n|Feb low F = 9\n|Mar low F = 21\n|Apr low F = 28\n|May low F = 35\n|Jun low F = 42\n|Jul low F = 48\n|Aug low F = 47\n|Sep low F = 38\n|Oct low F = 28\n|Nov low F = 17\n|Dec low F = 7\n|year low F = 27\n|Jan precipitation inch = 0.4\n|Feb precipitation inch = 0.4\n|Mar precipitation inch = 0.5\n|Apr precipitation inch = 0.8\n|May precipitation inch = 1.4\n|Jun precipitation inch = 0.9\n|Jul precipitation inch = 1\n|Aug precipitation inch = 0.9\n|Sep precipitation inch = 1.2\n|Oct precipitation inch = 1.3\n|Nov precipitation inch = 0.6\n|Dec precipitation inch = 0.6\n|year precipitation inch = 10.1\n|source 1 = Weatherbase <ref name=Weatherbase>\n{{cite web\n|url =http://www.weatherbase.com/weather/weather.php3?s=484084&cityname=Baggs-Wyoming-United-States-of-America\n|publisher=Weatherbase\n|title=Weatherbase.com\n|year=2013\n}}\nRetrieved on October 3, 2013.\n</ref>\n|date=October 2013\n}}\n\n==Education==\nPublic education in the town of Baggs is provided by [[Carbon County School District Number 1|Carbon County School District #1]]. [[Little Snake River Valley School]], a K-12 campus, serves the town.\n\nBaggs has a [[public library]], a branch of the Carbon County Library System.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://publiclibraries.com/state/wyoming/ | title=Wyoming Public Libraries | publisher=PublicLibraries.com | accessdate=13 June 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Notable people==\n* [[Earl W. Bascom]] (1906-1995), worked on a Baggs area ranch in 1927, rodeo champion, Hollywood actor, cowboy artist and sculptor\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of municipalities in Wyoming]]\n\n==References==\n<references />\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category|Baggs, Wyoming}}\n* {{official|http://www.townofbaggs.com}}\n* [https://www.littlesnakerivermuseum.com/outlaw_stop Outlaw Stop]\n\n\n{{Carbon County, Wyoming}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Towns in Carbon County, Wyoming]]\n[[Category:Towns in Wyoming]]\n", "name_user": "Holograham1355", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eNotable people", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Baggs,_Wyoming"}
{"title_page": "Tulcea County", "text_new": "{{short description|County of Romania}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n<!-- See Template:Infobox settlement for additional fields and descriptions -->\n| name                    = Tulcea County\n| native_name             = Jude\u021bul Tulcea\n| native_name_lang        = ro\n| settlement_type         = [[Counties of Romania|County]]\n| image_skyline           = \n| image_alt               = \n| image_caption           = \n| image_flag              = \n| flag_alt                = \n| image_seal              = \n| seal_alt                = \n| image_shield            = Actual_Tulcea_county_CoA.png\n| shield_alt              = \n| nickname                = \n| motto                   = \n| image_map               = Tulcea_in_Romania.svg\n| map_alt                 = Administrative map of [[Romania]] with Tulcea county highlighted\n| map_caption             = \n| pushpin_map             = \n| pushpin_map_alt         = \n| pushpin_map_caption     = \n| coordinates             = {{coord|44.98|28.77|type:adm1st_region:RO|display=inline,title}}\n| coor_pinpoint           = \n| coordinates_footnotes   = \n| subdivision_type        = Country\n| subdivision_name        = [[Romania]]\n| subdivision_type1       = Development region\n| subdivision_name1       = [[Sud-Est (development region)|Sud-Est]]\n| subdivision_type2       = Historical region\n| subdivision_name2       = [[Dobruja]]\n| established_title       = \n| established_date        = \n| founder                 = \n| seat_type               = Capital\n| seat                    = [[Tulcea]]\n| government_footnotes    = \n| leader_party            = \n| leader_title            = \n| leader_name             = \n| unit_pref               = Metric<!-- or US or UK -->\n| area_footnotes          = \n| area_total_km2          = 8,499\n| area_land_km2           = \n| area_water_km2          = \n| area_water_percent      = \n| area_note               = \n| area_rank               = [[List of Romanian counties by area|4th]]\n| elevation_footnotes     = \n| elevation_m             = \n| population_footnotes    = \n| population_total        = 201,462\n| population_as_of        = 2011\n| population_density_km2  = auto\n| population_demonym      = \n| population_note         = \n| population_rank         = [[List of Romanian counties by population|40th]]\n| timezone1               = \n| utc_offset1             = \n| timezone1_DST           = \n| utc_offset1_DST         = \n| postal_code_type        = \n| postal_code             = \n| area_code_type          = [[Telephone numbers in Romania|Telephone code]]\n| area_code               = (+40) 240 or (+40) 340<ref>The number used depends on the numbering system employed by the phone companies on the market.</ref>\n| iso_code                = RO-TL\n| website                 = [http://www.cjtulcea.ro/ County Council]<br />[http://www.prefecturatulcea.ro/ Prefecture]\n| footnotes               = \n| blank1_name             = GDP (nominal)\n| blank1_info             = US$ 1.378&nbsp;billion (''2015'') \n| blank2_name             = GDP/[[capita]]\n| blank2_info             = US$ 6,838 (''2015'')\n}}\n[[Image:Harta-judetului-Tulcea.jpg|260px|right|thumb|Map of Tulcea County.]]\n'''Tulcea County''' ({{IPA-ro|\u02c8tult\u0361\u0283e\u032fa}}) is a county ([[jude\u021b]]) of [[Romania]], in the historical region [[Dobruja]], with the capital city at [[Tulcea]].\n\n==Demographics==\nIn 2011, Tulcea County had a population of 201,462. The [[population density]] was 23.7/km\u00b2, the lowest among the [[counties of Romania]].\n\n*[[Romanians]] - 89.13%<ref>National Institute of Statistics, ''[http://www.recensamant.ro/pagini/tabele/t40a.pdf \"Popula\u021bia dup\u0103 etnie\"] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090816034908/http://www.recensamant.ro/pagini/tabele/t40a.pdf |date=2009-08-16 }}''</ref>\n*[[Lipovans]] - 5.41%\n*[[Turkish people|Turks]] - 0.93%\n*[[Romani people|Romani]] - 1.87%\n*[[Greeks]] - 0.65%\n\nIn the [[Danube Delta]] there is an important community of [[Russians]] and [[Lipovan]]s. In the south of the county there are communities of [[Turkish people|Turks]]. The region once was a centre of [[Islam in Romania]].\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! Year\n! County population<ref>National Institute of Statistics, ''[http://www.insse.ro/rpl2002rezgen/18.pdf \"Popula\u021bia la recens\u0103mintele din anii 1948, 1956, 1966, 1977, 1992 \u0219i 2002\"]''</ref>\n|- \n| 1948\n| 192,228\n|- \n| 1956\n|{{increase}} 223,719\n|- \n| 1966\n|{{increase}} 236,709\n|- \n| 1977\n|{{increase}} 254,531\n|- \n| 1992\n|{{increase}} 270,197\n|- \n| 2002\n|{{decrease}} 256,492\n|- \n| 2011\n|{{decrease}} 201,462\n|}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! Ethnicity\n! 2002<ref>[[National Institute of Statistics (Romania)|National Institute of Statistics]], [http://www.insse.ro/cms/files/RPL2002INS/vol4/tabele/t1.pdf 2002 census: Ethnic structure per county]</ref>\n|-\n| All\n| 256,492\n|-\n| Romanian\n| 230,843 (90%)\n|-\n| Lipovan\n| 16,350 (6.4%)\n|-\n| Turkish\n| 3,334 (1.3%)\n|-\n| Roma/Gypsy\n| 2,272 (0.9%)\n|-\n| Greek\n| 1,680 (0.7%)\n|-\n| Ukrainian\n| 1,279 (0.5%)\n|-\n| Tatar\n| 179 (0.1%)\n|-\n| Others\n| 555\n|}\n\n==Geography==\nThe county has a total area of 8,499&nbsp;km\u00b2.\n\n[[File:The Palace 02.jpg|thumb|right|upright|The Palace of the [[Commissions of the Danube River|Danube Commission]] in [[Sulina]], Tulcea County, Romania, from 1868 to 1921]]\n[[File:Isacceanoviodumun01.JPG|thumb|200px|Ruins of the Noviodunum fortress]]\nThe most significant feature of Tulcea County is the [[Danube Delta]], which occupies about 1/3 of the entire surface and is located in the North-East side of the county. The Delta has three main branches: the [[Sulina branch]] (the only one navigable by large ships) in the middle, the [[Chilia branch]] in the North (the border with [[Ukraine]]) and the [[Sf\u00e2ntu Gheorghe branch]] (Saint George) in the South.\n\nIn the South-East of the county there are two lagoons: [[Razelm Lake]] and [[Sinoe Lake]]. In the Danube Delta and in the South\u2014in the area between the Sf\u00e2ntu Gheorghe Channel and Razelm Lake\u2014there are countless channels and small lakes. The entire area is included in the [[UNESCO]] list of [[World Heritage Sites]] and [[Biosphere reserve]]s.\n\nThe [[Danube River]] flows around the county in the West and North side. In the West, there is the M\u0103cin Branch which flows on the East side of the [[Great Br\u0103ila Island]]. From [[Sm\u00e2rdan, Tulcea|Sm\u00e2rdan]] (on the opposite side from [[Br\u0103ila]]) to [[Ceatalchioi|P\u0103tl\u0103geanca]] (close to [[Tulcea]]), the Danube has only one big flow of water, around which there are an immense number of lakes and small channels.\n\nIn the center of the county, there is the Casincea Plateau and the [[M\u0103cin Mountains]]\u2014the remains of a prehistorical mountains range (more than 400 million years old), with the greatest height at about 400 m.\n\n===Neighbours===\n\n{{Romanian counties map|width=250px}}\n*[[Black Sea]] in the East.\n*[[Br\u0103ila County]] in the West.\n*[[Gala\u021bi County]] in the North-West\n*[[Ukraine]] in the North - the [[Odessa Oblast]].\n*[[Constan\u021ba County]] in the South.\n\n==Economy==\nAgriculture and fishing are the main occupations, involving about 48% of the population. Industry is concentrated in the large towns only.\n\nThe predominant industries in the county are:\n* Food industry.\n* Textile industry.\n* Ship building industry.\n* Metallurgy - [[aluminium]].\n* Chemical industry.\n* Construction materials.\n\n==Tourism==\nTourism is an important activity in the county, the [[Danube Delta]] being one of the most visited areas in [[Romania]].\n\nThe main destinations for tourists are:\n* The [[Danube Delta]]\n** The town of [[Sulina]]\u2014the last town on the [[Danube]].\n** The areas around [[Sf\u00e2ntu Gheorghe, Tulcea|Sf\u00e2ntu Gheorghe]], [[Mahmudia]], [[Cri\u0219an, Tulcea|Cri\u0219an]], Caraorman, [[Chilia Veche]].\n* The city of [[Tulcea]].\n* The Roman fort of [[Halmyris]].\n\n==Politics==\nThe Tulcea County Council, elected at the [[2016 Romanian local election|2016 local government elections]], is made up of 31 counselors, with the following party composition:<ref name=\"LocalElections2016\">{{cite web|url=http://www.2016bec.ro/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/SIAL2016_CJ_mandate.xlsx|title=Mandate de CJ pe judete si competitori|publisher=Biroul Electoral Central|date=10 June 2016|accessdate=16 June 2016|language=Romanian}}</ref>\n\n{| cellpadding=\"2\" cellspacing=\"0\" border=\"1\" class=\"wikitable\"\n! style=\"background:#ccc\" | &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n! style=\"background:#ccc\" | Party\n! style=\"background:#ccc\" | Seats\n! style=\"background:#ccc\" colspan=\"14\" | Current County Council\n|-\n| {{Romanian politics/party colours/PSD}} | &nbsp;\n| [[Social Democratic Party (Romania)|Social Democratic Party]]\n| style=\"text-align: right\" | '''14'''\n| {{Romanian politics/party colours/PSD}} | &nbsp;\n| {{Romanian politics/party colours/PSD}} | &nbsp;\n| {{Romanian politics/party colours/PSD}} | &nbsp;\n| {{Romanian politics/party colours/PSD}} | &nbsp;\n| {{Romanian politics/party colours/PSD}} | &nbsp;\n| {{Romanian politics/party colours/PSD}} | &nbsp;\n| {{Romanian politics/party colours/PSD}} | &nbsp;\n| {{Romanian politics/party colours/PSD}} | &nbsp;\n| {{Romanian politics/party colours/PSD}} | &nbsp;\n| {{Romanian politics/party colours/PSD}} | &nbsp;\n| {{Romanian politics/party colours/PSD}} | &nbsp;\n| {{Romanian politics/party colours/PSD}} | &nbsp;\n| {{Romanian politics/party colours/PSD}} | &nbsp;\n| {{Romanian politics/party colours/PSD}} | &nbsp;\n|-\n| {{Romanian politics/party colours/PNL}} | &nbsp;\n| [[National Liberal Party (Romania)|National Liberal Party]]\n| style=\"text-align: right\" | '''12'''\n| {{Romanian politics/party colours/PNL}} | &nbsp;\n| {{Romanian politics/party colours/PNL}} | &nbsp;\n| {{Romanian politics/party colours/PNL}} | &nbsp;\n| {{Romanian politics/party colours/PNL}} | &nbsp;\n| {{Romanian politics/party colours/PNL}} | &nbsp;\n| {{Romanian politics/party colours/PNL}} | &nbsp;\n| {{Romanian politics/party colours/PNL}} | &nbsp;\n| {{Romanian politics/party colours/PNL}} | &nbsp;\n| {{Romanian politics/party colours/PNL}} | &nbsp;\n| {{Romanian politics/party colours/PNL}} | &nbsp;\n| {{Romanian politics/party colours/PNL}} | &nbsp;\n| {{Romanian politics/party colours/PNL}} | &nbsp;\n| &nbsp;\n| &nbsp;\n|-\n| {{Romanian politics/party colours/ALDE}} | &nbsp;\n| [[Alliance of Liberals and Democrats (Romania)|Alliance of Liberals and Democrats]]\n| style=\"text-align: right\" | '''3'''\n| {{Romanian politics/party colours/ALDE}} | &nbsp;\n| {{Romanian politics/party colours/ALDE}} | &nbsp;\n| {{Romanian politics/party colours/ALDE}} | &nbsp;\n| &nbsp;\n| &nbsp;\n| &nbsp;\n| &nbsp;\n| &nbsp;\n| &nbsp;\n| &nbsp;\n| &nbsp;\n| &nbsp;\n| &nbsp;\n| &nbsp;\n|-\n| {{Romanian politics/party colours/PMP}} | &nbsp;\n| [[People's Movement Party]]\n| style=\"text-align: right\" | '''2'''\n| {{Romanian politics/party colours/PMP}} | &nbsp;\n| {{Romanian politics/party colours/PMP}} | &nbsp;\n| &nbsp;\n| &nbsp;\n| &nbsp;\n| &nbsp;\n| &nbsp;\n| &nbsp;\n| &nbsp;\n| &nbsp;\n| &nbsp;\n| &nbsp;\n| &nbsp;\n| &nbsp;\n|}\n\n==Administrative divisions==\n[[File:Tulcea_harbour_01.jpg|thumb|[[Tulcea]] harbour]]\nTulcea County has 1 municipality, 4 towns and 46 communes.\n;Municipalities\n*[[Tulcea]] - capital city; population: 92,379 (as of 2007)\n;Towns\n{{columns-list|colwidth=18em|\n*[[Babadag]]\n*[[Isaccea]]\n*[[M\u0103cin]]\n*[[Sulina]]\n}}\n;Communes\n{{columns-list|colwidth=18em|\n*[[Baia, Tulcea|Baia]]\n*[[Baidaud]]\n*[[Be\u0219tepe, Tulcea|Be\u0219tepe]]\n*[[C. A. Rosetti, Tulcea|C. A. Rosetti]]\n*[[Carcaliu]]\n*[[Casimcea]]\n*[[Ceamurlia de Jos]]\n*[[Ceatalchioi]]\n*[[Cerna, Tulcea|Cerna]]\n*[[Chilia Veche]]\n*[[Ciucurova]]\n*[[Cri\u0219an, Tulcea|Cri\u0219an]]\n*[[D\u0103eni]]\n*[[Doroban\u021bu, Tulcea|Doroban\u021bu]]\n*[[Frec\u0103\u021bei, Tulcea|Frec\u0103\u021bei]]\n*[[Greci, Tulcea|Greci]]\n*[[Grindu, Tulcea|Grindu]]\n*[[Hamcearca]]\n*[[Horia, Tulcea|Horia]]\n*[[I. C. Br\u0103tianu, Tulcea|I. C. Br\u0103tianu]] (Zacl\u0103u, 23 August)\n*[[Izvoarele, Tulcea|Izvoarele]]\n*[[Jijila]]\n*[[Jurilovca]] (Unirea)\n*[[Luncavi\u021ba, Tulcea|Luncavi\u021ba]]\n*[[Mahmudia]]\n*[[Maliuc]]\n*[[Mihai Bravu, Tulcea|Mihai Bravu]]\n*[[Mihail Kog\u0103lniceanu, Tulcea|Mihai Kog\u0103lniceanu]]\n*[[Murighiol]] (Independen\u021ba)\n*[[Nalbant]]\n*[[Niculi\u021bel]]\n*[[Nuf\u0103ru]]\n*[[Ostrov, Tulcea|Ostrov]]\n*[[Pardina, Tulcea|Pardina]] (1 Mai)\n*[[Peceneaga]]\n*[[Sarichioi]]\n*[[Sf\u00e2ntu Gheorghe, Tulcea|Sf\u00e2ntu Gheorghe]]\n*[[Slava Cerchez\u0103]]\n*[[Sm\u0103rdan]]\n*[[Somova]]\n*[[Stejaru, Tulcea|Stejaru]]\n*[[Topolog, Tulcea|Topolog]]\n*[[Turcoaia]]\n*[[Valea Nucarilor]]\n*[[Valea Teilor]]\n*[[V\u0103c\u0103reni]]\n}}\n\n==Historical county==\n{{Infobox settlement\n | official_name          = Jude\u021bul Tulcea\n | other_name             = \n | settlement_type        = County (''Jude\u021b'')\n | image_skyline          = Palatul Pasei de Tulcea - Muzeul de Arta.jpg\n | image_caption          = The Tulcea prefecture building from the interwar period, now the [[Tulcea Art Museum]].\n | image_flag             = \n | flag_link              = \n | image_shield           = Interbelic Tulcea County CoA.png\n | shield_link            = \n | image_map              = Romania 1930 county Tulcea.png\n | map_caption            = \n | subdivision_type       = [[Countries of the world|Country]]\n | subdivision_name       = [[Image:Flag of Romania.svg|25px]] [[Kingdom of Romania|Romania]]\n | subdivision_type2      = Historic region\n | subdivision_name2      = [[Dobrogea]]\n | subdivision_type3      = Capital city (''Re\u0219edin\u021b\u0103 de jude\u021b'')\n | subdivision_name3      = [[Tulcea]]\n | government_footnotes   = \n | government_type        = \n | leader_party           = \n | leader_title           = [[Prefect (Romania)|Prefect]]\n | leader_name            = \n | leader_title1          = \n | leader_name1           = \n | established_title      = Established\n | established_date       = \n | established_title2     = Ceased to exist\n | established_date2      = \n | area_total_km2         = 8628\n | area_land_km2          = \n | area_water_km2         = \n | area_water_percent     = \n | elevation_footnotes    = \n | elevation_m            = \n | population_as_of       = 1930\n | population_footnotes   = \n | population_total       = 184038\n | population_density_km2 = auto\n | population_note        = \n | timezone               = [[Eastern European Time|EET]]\n | utc_offset             = +2\n | timezone_DST           = [[Eastern European Summer Time|EEST]]\n | utc_offset_DST         = +3\n | postal_code_type       = \n | postal_code            = \n | area_code              = \n | footnotes              = \n | website                = \n}}\nHistorically, the county was located in the southeastern part of [[Greater Romania]], in the region of north [[Dobruja]]. The borders of the historic county coincide with those of the present county. It bordered on the west with [[Br\u0103ila County]], northwest with [[Covurlui County]], to the north with [[Ismail County]], to the south by [[Constan\u021ba County]], and to the east and south-east with the [[Black Sea]].\n\n===Administration===\n[[File:1938 map of interwar county Tulcea.jpg|thumb|right|350px|Map of Tulcea County as constituted in 1938.]]\nThe county was originally divided administratively into four districts (''[[plas\u0103|pl\u0103\u1e63i]]''):<ref name=Memoria>[http://romaniainterbelica.memoria.ro/judete/tulcea/ Portretul Rom\u00e2niei Interbelice - Jude\u021bul Tulcea]</ref>\n#Plasa Babadag, headquartered at [[Babadag]]\n#Plasa Gurile Dun\u0103rii, headquartered at [[Tulcea]]\n#Plasa M\u0103cin, headquartered at [[M\u0103cin]]\n#Plasa Topolog, headquartered at [[Topolog, Tulcea|Topolog]]\n\nAs in the present day there were five towns (cities): [[Tulcea]] (county headquarters), [[Babadag]], [[M\u0103cin]], [[Isaccea]] and [[Sulina]].\n\n=== Population ===\n[[File:Ethnic map of Tulcea County 1930.png|thumb|right|350px|Map of Tulcea County's ethnic groups as reported in the 1930 census.]]\nAccording to the 1930 census data, the county population was 184,038 inhabitants, ethnically divided as follows: 62.6% Romanians, 12.2% Russians, 10.6% Bulgarians, 2.5% Turks, 1.7% Greeks, 1.3% Germans, as well as other minorities.<ref name=Rec_1930_480>Recens\u0103m\u00e2ntul general al popula\u021biei Rom\u00e2niei din 29 decemvrie 1930, Vol. II, pag. 480</ref> From the religious point of view, the population was 85.8% Eastern Orthodox, 8.3% [[Lipovan Orthodox Old-Rite Church|Old-Rite Lipovan Orthodox]], 2.8% Muslim, 1.5% Roman Catholic, 0.6% Lutheran, as well as other minorities.\n\n==== Urban population ====\nIn 1930, the county's urban population was 41,632 inhabitants, comprising 64.7% Romanians, 12.8% Russians, 5.5% Turks, 4.4% Greeks, 3.3% Bulgarians, 2.5% Jews, 0.8% Germans, as well as other minorities. Mother tongues among the urban population were Romanian (69.4%), followed by Russian (15.0%), Turkish (5.5%), Greek (3.9%), Yiddish (1.5%), as well as other minorities.<ref name=Rec_1930_480/> From the religious point of view, the urban population was composed of 87.5% Eastern Orthodox, 5.7% Muslim, 2.6% Jewish, 1.9% Roman Catholic, as well as other minorities.\n\n==References==\n{{commons category|Tulcea County}}\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n\n{{Tulcea County}}\n{{Counties (judete) of Romania}}\n\n[[Category:Tulcea County| ]]\n[[Category:Counties of Romania]]\n[[Category:1879 establishments in Romania]]\n[[Category:1938 disestablishments in Romania]]\n[[Category:1940 establishments in Romania]]\n[[Category:1950 disestablishments in Romania]]\n[[Category:1968 establishments in Romania]]\n[[Category:States and territories established in 1879]]\n[[Category:States and territories disestablished in 1938]]\n[[Category:States and territories established in 1940]]\n[[Category:States and territories disestablished in 1950]]\n[[Category:States and territories established in 1968]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|County of Romania}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n<!-- See Template:Infobox settlement for additional fields and descriptions -->\n| name                    = Tulcea County\n| native_name             = Jude\u021bul Tulcea\n| native_name_lang        = ro\n| settlement_type         = [[Counties of Romania|County]]\n| image_skyline           = \n| image_alt               = \n| image_caption           = \n| image_flag              = \n| flag_alt                = \n| image_seal              = \n| seal_alt                = \n| image_shield            = Actual_Tulcea_county_CoA.png\n| shield_alt              = \n| nickname                = \n| motto                   = \n| image_map               = Tulcea_in_Romania.svg\n| map_alt                 = Administrative map of [[Romania]] with Tulcea county highlighted\n| map_caption             = \n| pushpin_map             = \n| pushpin_map_alt         = \n| pushpin_map_caption     = \n| coordinates             = {{coord|44.98|28.77|type:adm1st_region:RO|display=inline,title}}\n| coor_pinpoint           = \n| coordinates_footnotes   = \n| subdivision_type        = Country\n| subdivision_name        = [[Romania]]\n| subdivision_type1       = Development region\n| subdivision_name1       = [[Sud-Est (development region)|Sud-Est]]\n| subdivision_type2       = Historical region\n| subdivision_name2       = [[Dobruja]]\n| established_title       = \n| established_date        = \n| founder                 = \n| seat_type               = Capital\n| seat                    = [[Tulcea]]\n| government_footnotes    = \n| leader_party            = \n| leader_title            = \n| leader_name             = \n| unit_pref               = Metric<!-- or US or UK -->\n| area_footnotes          = \n| area_total_km2          = 8,499\n| area_land_km2           = \n| area_water_km2          = \n| area_water_percent      = \n| area_note               = \n| area_rank               = [[List of Romanian counties by area|4th]]\n| elevation_footnotes     = \n| elevation_m             = \n| population_footnotes    = \n| population_total        = 201,462\n| population_as_of        = 2011\n| population_density_km2  = auto\n| population_demonym      = \n| population_note         = \n| population_rank         = [[List of Romanian counties by population|40th]]\n| timezone1               = \n| utc_offset1             = \n| timezone1_DST           = \n| utc_offset1_DST         = \n| postal_code_type        = \n| postal_code             = \n| area_code_type          = [[Telephone numbers in Romania|Telephone code]]\n| area_code               = (+40) 240 or (+40) 340<ref>The number used depends on the numbering system employed by the phone companies on the market.</ref>\n| iso_code                = RO-TL\n| website                 = [http://www.cjtulcea.ro/ County Council]<br />[http://www.prefecturatulcea.ro/ Prefecture]\n| footnotes               = \n| blank1_name             = GDP (nominal)\n| blank1_info             = US$ 1.378&nbsp;billion (''2015'') \n| blank2_name             = GDP/[[capita]]\n| blank2_info             = US$ 6,838 (''2015'')\n}}\n[[Image:Harta-judetului-Tulcea.jpg|260px|right|thumb|Map of Tulcea County.]]\n'''Tulcea County''' ({{IPA-ro|\u02c8tult\u0361\u0283e\u032fa}}) is a county ([[jude\u021b]]) of [[Romania]], in the historical region [[Dobruja]], with the capital city at [[Tulcea]].\n\n==Demographics==\nIn 2011, Tulcea County had a population of 201,462. The [[population density]] was 23.7/km\u00b2, the lowest among the [[counties of Romania]].\n\n*[[Romanians]] - 89.13%<ref>National Institute of Statistics, ''[http://www.recensamant.ro/pagini/tabele/t40a.pdf \"Popula\u021bia dup\u0103 etnie\"] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090816034908/http://www.recensamant.ro/pagini/tabele/t40a.pdf |date=2009-08-16 }}''</ref>\n*[[Lipovans]] - 5.41%\n*[[Turkish people|Turks]] - 0.93%\n*[[Romani people|Romani]] - 1.87%\n*[[Greeks]] - 0.65%\n\nIn the [[Danube Delta]] there is an important community of [[Russians]] and [[Lipovan]]s. In the south of the county there are communities of [[Turkish people|Turks]]. The region once was a centre of [[Islam in Romania]].\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! Year\n! County population<ref>National Institute of Statistics, ''[http://www.insse.ro/rpl2002rezgen/18.pdf \"Popula\u021bia la recens\u0103mintele din anii 1948, 1956, 1966, 1977, 1992 \u0219i 2002\"]''</ref>\n|- \n| 1948\n| 192,228\n|- \n| 1956\n|{{increase}} 223,719\n|- \n| 1966\n|{{increase}} 236,709\n|- \n| 1977\n|{{increase}} 254,531\n|- \n| 1992\n|{{increase}} 270,197\n|- \n| 2002\n|{{decrease}} 256,492\n|- \n| 2011\n|{{decrease}} 201,462\n|}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! Ethnicity\n! 2002<ref>[[National Institute of Statistics (Romania)|National Institute of Statistics]], [http://www.insse.ro/cms/files/RPL2002INS/vol4/tabele/t1.pdf 2002 census: Ethnic structure per county]</ref>\n|-\n| All\n| 256,492\n|-\n| Romanian\n| 230,843 (90%)\n|-\n| Lipovan\n| 16,350 (6.4%)\n|-\n| Turkish\n| 3,334 (1.3%)\n|-\n| Roma/Gypsy\n| 2,272 (0.9%)\n|-\n| Greek\n| 1,680 (0.7%)\n|-\n| Ukrainian\n| 1,279 (0.5%)\n|-\n| Tatar\n| 179 (0.1%)\n|-\n| Others\n| 555\n|}\n\n==Geography==\nThe county has a total area of 8,499&nbsp;km\u00b2.\n\n[[File:The Palace 02.jpg|thumb|right|upright|The Palace of the [[Commissions of the Danube River|Danube Commission]] in [[Sulina]], Tulcea County, Romania, from 1868 to 1921]]\n[[File:Isacceanoviodumun01.JPG|thumb|200px|Ruins of the Noviodunum fortress]]\nThe most significant feature of Tulcea County is the [[Danube Delta]], which occupies about 1/3 of the entire surface and is located in the North-East side of the county. The Delta has three main branches: the [[Sulina branch]] (the only one navigable by large ships) in the middle, the [[Chilia branch]] in the North (the border with [[Ukraine]]) and the [[Sf\u00e2ntu Gheorghe branch]] (Saint George) in the South.\n\nIn the South-East of the county there are two lagoons: [[Razelm Lake]] and [[Sinoe Lake]]. In the Danube Delta and in the South\u2014in the area between the Sf\u00e2ntu Gheorghe Channel and Razelm Lake\u2014there are countless channels and small lakes. The entire area is  included in the [[UNESCO]] list of [[World Heritage Sites]] and [[Biosphere reserve]]s.\n\nThe [[Danube River]] flows around the county in the West and North side. In the West there is the M\u0103cin Branch which flows on the East side of the [[Great Br\u0103ila Island]]. From [[Sm\u00e2rdan, Tulcea|Sm\u00e2rdan]] (on the opposite side from [[Br\u0103ila]]) to [[Ceatalchioi|P\u0103tl\u0103geanca]] (close to [[Tulcea]]), the Danube has only one big flow of water, around which there are an immense number of lakes and small channels.\n\nIn the center of the county there is the Casincea Plateau and the [[M\u0103cin Mountains]]\u2014the remains of a prehistorical mountains range (more than 400 million years old), with the greatest height at about 400 m.\n\n===Neighbours===\n\n{{Romanian counties map|width=250px}}\n*[[Black Sea]] in the East.\n*[[Br\u0103ila County]] in the West.\n*[[Gala\u021bi County]] in the North-West\n*[[Ukraine]] in the North - the [[Odessa Oblast]].\n*[[Constan\u021ba County]] in the South.\n\n==Economy==\nAgriculture and fishing are the main occupations, involving about 48% of the population. Industry is concentrated in the large towns only.\n\nThe predominant industries in the county are:\n* Food industry.\n* Textile industry.\n* Ship building industry.\n* Metallurgy - [[aluminium]].\n* Chemical industry.\n* Construction materials.\n\n==Tourism==\nTourism is an important activity in the county, the [[Danube Delta]] being one of the most visited areas in [[Romania]].\n\nThe main destinations for tourists are:\n* The [[Danube Delta]]\n** The town of [[Sulina]]\u2014the last town on the [[Danube]].\n** The areas around [[Sf\u00e2ntu Gheorghe, Tulcea|Sf\u00e2ntu Gheorghe]], [[Mahmudia]], [[Cri\u0219an, Tulcea|Cri\u0219an]], Caraorman, [[Chilia Veche]].\n* The city of [[Tulcea]].\n* The Roman fort of [[Halmyris]].\n\n==Politics==\nThe Tulcea County Council, elected at the [[2016 Romanian local election|2016 local government elections]], is made up of 31 counselors, with the following party composition:<ref name=\"LocalElections2016\">{{cite web|url=http://www.2016bec.ro/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/SIAL2016_CJ_mandate.xlsx|title=Mandate de CJ pe judete si competitori|publisher=Biroul Electoral Central|date=10 June 2016|accessdate=16 June 2016|language=Romanian}}</ref>\n\n{| cellpadding=\"2\" cellspacing=\"0\" border=\"1\" class=\"wikitable\"\n! style=\"background:#ccc\" | &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n! style=\"background:#ccc\" | Party\n! style=\"background:#ccc\" | Seats\n! style=\"background:#ccc\" colspan=\"14\" | Current County Council\n|-\n| {{Romanian politics/party colours/PSD}} | &nbsp;\n| [[Social Democratic Party (Romania)|Social Democratic Party]]\n| style=\"text-align: right\" | '''14'''\n| {{Romanian politics/party colours/PSD}} | &nbsp;\n| {{Romanian politics/party colours/PSD}} | &nbsp;\n| {{Romanian politics/party colours/PSD}} | &nbsp;\n| {{Romanian politics/party colours/PSD}} | &nbsp;\n| {{Romanian politics/party colours/PSD}} | &nbsp;\n| {{Romanian politics/party colours/PSD}} | &nbsp;\n| {{Romanian politics/party colours/PSD}} | &nbsp;\n| {{Romanian politics/party colours/PSD}} | &nbsp;\n| {{Romanian politics/party colours/PSD}} | &nbsp;\n| {{Romanian politics/party colours/PSD}} | &nbsp;\n| {{Romanian politics/party colours/PSD}} | &nbsp;\n| {{Romanian politics/party colours/PSD}} | &nbsp;\n| {{Romanian politics/party colours/PSD}} | &nbsp;\n| {{Romanian politics/party colours/PSD}} | &nbsp;\n|-\n| {{Romanian politics/party colours/PNL}} | &nbsp;\n| [[National Liberal Party (Romania)|National Liberal Party]]\n| style=\"text-align: right\" | '''12'''\n| {{Romanian politics/party colours/PNL}} | &nbsp;\n| {{Romanian politics/party colours/PNL}} | &nbsp;\n| {{Romanian politics/party colours/PNL}} | &nbsp;\n| {{Romanian politics/party colours/PNL}} | &nbsp;\n| {{Romanian politics/party colours/PNL}} | &nbsp;\n| {{Romanian politics/party colours/PNL}} | &nbsp;\n| {{Romanian politics/party colours/PNL}} | &nbsp;\n| {{Romanian politics/party colours/PNL}} | &nbsp;\n| {{Romanian politics/party colours/PNL}} | &nbsp;\n| {{Romanian politics/party colours/PNL}} | &nbsp;\n| {{Romanian politics/party colours/PNL}} | &nbsp;\n| {{Romanian politics/party colours/PNL}} | &nbsp;\n| &nbsp;\n| &nbsp;\n|-\n| {{Romanian politics/party colours/ALDE}} | &nbsp;\n| [[Alliance of Liberals and Democrats (Romania)|Alliance of Liberals and Democrats]]\n| style=\"text-align: right\" | '''3'''\n| {{Romanian politics/party colours/ALDE}} | &nbsp;\n| {{Romanian politics/party colours/ALDE}} | &nbsp;\n| {{Romanian politics/party colours/ALDE}} | &nbsp;\n| &nbsp;\n| &nbsp;\n| &nbsp;\n| &nbsp;\n| &nbsp;\n| &nbsp;\n| &nbsp;\n| &nbsp;\n| &nbsp;\n| &nbsp;\n| &nbsp;\n|-\n| {{Romanian politics/party colours/PMP}} | &nbsp;\n| [[People's Movement Party]]\n| style=\"text-align: right\" | '''2'''\n| {{Romanian politics/party colours/PMP}} | &nbsp;\n| {{Romanian politics/party colours/PMP}} | &nbsp;\n| &nbsp;\n| &nbsp;\n| &nbsp;\n| &nbsp;\n| &nbsp;\n| &nbsp;\n| &nbsp;\n| &nbsp;\n| &nbsp;\n| &nbsp;\n| &nbsp;\n| &nbsp;\n|}\n\n==Administrative divisions==\n[[File:Tulcea_harbour_01.jpg|thumb|[[Tulcea]] harbour]]\nTulcea County has 1 municipality, 4 towns and 46 communes.\n;Municipalities\n*[[Tulcea]] - capital city; population: 92,379 (as of 2007)\n;Towns\n{{columns-list|colwidth=18em|\n*[[Babadag]]\n*[[Isaccea]]\n*[[M\u0103cin]]\n*[[Sulina]]\n}}\n;Communes\n{{columns-list|colwidth=18em|\n*[[Baia, Tulcea|Baia]]\n*[[Baidaud]]\n*[[Be\u0219tepe, Tulcea|Be\u0219tepe]]\n*[[C. A. Rosetti, Tulcea|C. A. Rosetti]]\n*[[Carcaliu]]\n*[[Casimcea]]\n*[[Ceamurlia de Jos]]\n*[[Ceatalchioi]]\n*[[Cerna, Tulcea|Cerna]]\n*[[Chilia Veche]]\n*[[Ciucurova]]\n*[[Cri\u0219an, Tulcea|Cri\u0219an]]\n*[[D\u0103eni]]\n*[[Doroban\u021bu, Tulcea|Doroban\u021bu]]\n*[[Frec\u0103\u021bei, Tulcea|Frec\u0103\u021bei]]\n*[[Greci, Tulcea|Greci]]\n*[[Grindu, Tulcea|Grindu]]\n*[[Hamcearca]]\n*[[Horia, Tulcea|Horia]]\n*[[I. C. Br\u0103tianu, Tulcea|I. C. Br\u0103tianu]] (Zacl\u0103u, 23 August)\n*[[Izvoarele, Tulcea|Izvoarele]]\n*[[Jijila]]\n*[[Jurilovca]] (Unirea)\n*[[Luncavi\u021ba, Tulcea|Luncavi\u021ba]]\n*[[Mahmudia]]\n*[[Maliuc]]\n*[[Mihai Bravu, Tulcea|Mihai Bravu]]\n*[[Mihail Kog\u0103lniceanu, Tulcea|Mihai Kog\u0103lniceanu]]\n*[[Murighiol]] (Independen\u021ba)\n*[[Nalbant]]\n*[[Niculi\u021bel]]\n*[[Nuf\u0103ru]]\n*[[Ostrov, Tulcea|Ostrov]]\n*[[Pardina, Tulcea|Pardina]] (1 Mai)\n*[[Peceneaga]]\n*[[Sarichioi]]\n*[[Sf\u00e2ntu Gheorghe, Tulcea|Sf\u00e2ntu Gheorghe]]\n*[[Slava Cerchez\u0103]]\n*[[Sm\u0103rdan]]\n*[[Somova]]\n*[[Stejaru, Tulcea|Stejaru]]\n*[[Topolog, Tulcea|Topolog]]\n*[[Turcoaia]]\n*[[Valea Nucarilor]]\n*[[Valea Teilor]]\n*[[V\u0103c\u0103reni]]\n}}\n\n==Historical county==\n{{Infobox settlement\n | official_name          = Jude\u021bul Tulcea\n | other_name             = \n | settlement_type        = County (''Jude\u021b'')\n | image_skyline          = Palatul Pasei de Tulcea - Muzeul de Arta.jpg\n | image_caption          = The Tulcea prefecture building from the interwar period, now the [[Tulcea Art Museum]].\n | image_flag             = \n | flag_link              = \n | image_shield           = Interbelic Tulcea County CoA.png\n | shield_link            = \n | image_map              = Romania 1930 county Tulcea.png\n | map_caption            = \n | subdivision_type       = [[Countries of the world|Country]]\n | subdivision_name       = [[Image:Flag of Romania.svg|25px]] [[Kingdom of Romania|Romania]]\n | subdivision_type2      = Historic region\n | subdivision_name2      = [[Dobrogea]]\n | subdivision_type3      = Capital city (''Re\u0219edin\u021b\u0103 de jude\u021b'')\n | subdivision_name3      = [[Tulcea]]\n | government_footnotes   = \n | government_type        = \n | leader_party           = \n | leader_title           = [[Prefect (Romania)|Prefect]]\n | leader_name            = \n | leader_title1          = \n | leader_name1           = \n | established_title      = Established\n | established_date       = \n | established_title2     = Ceased to exist\n | established_date2      = \n | area_total_km2         = 8628\n | area_land_km2          = \n | area_water_km2         = \n | area_water_percent     = \n | elevation_footnotes    = \n | elevation_m            = \n | population_as_of       = 1930\n | population_footnotes   = \n | population_total       = 184038\n | population_density_km2 = auto\n | population_note        = \n | timezone               = [[Eastern European Time|EET]]\n | utc_offset             = +2\n | timezone_DST           = [[Eastern European Summer Time|EEST]]\n | utc_offset_DST         = +3\n | postal_code_type       = \n | postal_code            = \n | area_code              = \n | footnotes              = \n | website                = \n}}\nHistorically, the county was located in the southeastern part of [[Greater Romania]], in the region of north [[Dobruja]]. The borders of the historic county coincide with those of the present county. It bordered on the west with [[Br\u0103ila County]], northwest with [[Covurlui County]], to the north with [[Ismail County]], to the south by [[Constan\u021ba County]], and to the east and south-east with the [[Black Sea]].\n\n===Administration===\n[[File:1938 map of interwar county Tulcea.jpg|thumb|right|350px|Map of Tulcea County as constituted in 1938.]]\nThe county was originally divided administratively into four districts (''[[plas\u0103|pl\u0103\u1e63i]]''):<ref name=Memoria>[http://romaniainterbelica.memoria.ro/judete/tulcea/ Portretul Rom\u00e2niei Interbelice - Jude\u021bul Tulcea]</ref>\n#Plasa Babadag, headquartered at [[Babadag]]\n#Plasa Gurile Dun\u0103rii, headquartered at [[Tulcea]]\n#Plasa M\u0103cin, headquartered at [[M\u0103cin]]\n#Plasa Topolog, headquartered at [[Topolog, Tulcea|Topolog]]\n\nAs in the present day there were five towns (cities): [[Tulcea]] (county headquarters), [[Babadag]], [[M\u0103cin]], [[Isaccea]] and [[Sulina]].\n\n=== Population ===\n[[File:Ethnic map of Tulcea County 1930.png|thumb|right|350px|Map of Tulcea County's ethnic groups as reported in the 1930 census.]]\nAccording to the 1930 census data, the county population was 184,038 inhabitants, ethnically divided as follows: 62.6% Romanians, 12.2% Russians, 10.6% Bulgarians, 2.5% Turks, 1.7% Greeks, 1.3% Germans, as well as other minorities.<ref name=Rec_1930_480>Recens\u0103m\u00e2ntul general al popula\u021biei Rom\u00e2niei din 29 decemvrie 1930, Vol. II, pag. 480</ref> From the religious point of view, the population was 85.8% Eastern Orthodox, 8.3% [[Lipovan Orthodox Old-Rite Church|Old-Rite Lipovan Orthodox]], 2.8% Muslim, 1.5% Roman Catholic, 0.6% Lutheran, as well as other minorities.\n\n==== Urban population ====\nIn 1930, the county's urban population was 41,632 inhabitants, comprising 64.7% Romanians, 12.8% Russians, 5.5% Turks, 4.4% Greeks, 3.3% Bulgarians, 2.5% Jews, 0.8% Germans, as well as other minorities. Mother tongues among the urban population were Romanian (69.4%), followed by Russian (15.0%), Turkish (5.5%), Greek (3.9%), Yiddish (1.5%), as well as other minorities.<ref name=Rec_1930_480/> From the religious point of view, the urban population was composed of 87.5% Eastern Orthodox, 5.7% Muslim, 2.6% Jewish, 1.9% Roman Catholic, as well as other minorities.\n\n==References==\n{{commons category|Tulcea County}}\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n\n{{Tulcea County}}\n{{Counties (judete) of Romania}}\n\n[[Category:Tulcea County| ]]\n[[Category:Counties of Romania]]\n[[Category:1879 establishments in Romania]]\n[[Category:1938 disestablishments in Romania]]\n[[Category:1940 establishments in Romania]]\n[[Category:1950 disestablishments in Romania]]\n[[Category:1968 establishments in Romania]]\n[[Category:States and territories established in 1879]]\n[[Category:States and territories disestablished in 1938]]\n[[Category:States and territories established in 1940]]\n[[Category:States and territories disestablished in 1950]]\n[[Category:States and territories established in 1968]]\n", "name_user": "Shadow Soap", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tulcea_County"}
{"title_page": "AIRES Flight 8250", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2019}}\n{{Infobox aircraft occurrence\n| image = AIRES-737-700.JPG\n| image_upright = \n| alt = \n| caption = HK-4682, the aircraft involved, seen at [[Bogot\u00e1 Airport]] five months before the crash\n| occurrence_type = Accident\n| date = {{Start date|2010|08|16|df=y}}\n| summary = [[Controlled flight into terrain | Runway undershoot]] due to [[pilot error]], aggravated by the [[Sensory_illusions_in_aviation#Black-hole_approach|black hole approach illusion]].<ref>''[[Mayday (Canadian TV series) | Mayday]]''. Season 20 Episode 5, \"Runway Breakup\".</ref>\n| site = [[Gustavo Rojas Pinilla International Airport]], [[San Andr\u00e9s, San Andr\u00e9s y Providencia|San Andr\u00e9s]], Colombia\n| coordinates = {{coord|12|34|45|N|81|43|10|W|source:kolossus-ptwiki_type:event|display=inline,title}}\n| aircraft_type = [[Boeing 737-700|Boeing 737-73V]]\n| aircraft_name = \n| operator = [[AIRES]]\n| IATA = \n| ICAO = ARE8250\n| callsign = \n| tail_number = HK-4682\n| origin = [[El Dorado International Airport]], [[Bogot\u00e1]], Colombia\n| destination = [[Gustavo Rojas Pinilla International Airport]], [[San Andr\u00e9s (island)|San Andr\u00e9s]], Colombia\n| occupants = 131\n| passengers = 125\n| crew = 6\n| fatalities= 2\n| injuries = 129\n| survivors = 129\n}}\n\n'''AIRES Flight 8250''' was a domestic scheduled passenger flight that on 16 August 2010 crashed on landing at night in poor weather on the Colombian island of [[San Andr\u00e9s (island)|San Andr\u00e9s]], killing 2 of the 131 people on board. The aircraft, an [[AIRES]]-operated [[Boeing 737-700]], was arriving from the Colombian capital [[Bogot\u00e1]] when it heavily touched down short of the runway, breaking up in three sections.\n\nThe official investigation concluded that the crash was caused by the misjudgement by the crew of the aircraft's altitude during the last phase of the approach.<ref name=\"Final report\">{{cite report |title=Accidente ocurrido el d\u00eda 16 de Agosto de 2010 a  la aeronave Boeing 737-700, Matr\u00edcula HK-4682 en el Aeropuerto Internacional Gustavo Rojas Pinilla de la Isla de San Andr\u00e9s - Colombia |url=http://reports.aviation-safety.net/2010/20100816-0_B737_HK-4682.pdf |accessdate=22 September 2019 |publisher=[[UAEAC]]}}</ref>\n\n== History of the flight ==\nFlight 8250 was operated by the local, privately owned Colombian airline [[AIRES]].<ref name=Reuters16Aug2010CrashesDuringStorm/><ref name=BBC16Aug2010PlaneBreaks/> The aircraft was on a flight from Bogot\u00e1 to the Colombian island of [[San Andr\u00e9s (island)|San Andr\u00e9s]], in the [[Caribbean]].<ref name=BBC16Aug2010PlaneBreaks/> A popular tourist destination, San Andres Island is about {{convert|190|km|mi nmi|abbr=}} east of the Nicaraguan coast.<ref name=BBC16Aug2010PlaneBreaks/>\n\nThe flight took off from Bogot\u00e1's [[El Dorado International Airport]] at 00:07 en route to [[Gustavo Rojas Pinilla International Airport]] with 125 passengers and six crew. [[pilot in command|Captain]] Wilson Gutierrez was the pilot flying (PF) while [[first officer (aeronautics)|First Officer]] Camilo Pineyros Rodriguez was pilot monitoring (PM).<ref name=RCN16Aug2010/>\n\n=== Accident ===\nThe crash occurred as the aircraft landed at San Andr\u00e9s at 1:49&nbsp;am local Western Caribbean Time ([[UTC\u221205:00]]).<ref name=BBC16Aug2010PlaneBreaks/><ref name=CNN16Aug2010JetSplitsApart/> The Boeing 737 broke up into three main sections.<ref name=AviationHerald/> The impact occurred about {{convert|260|ft|m|-1}} before the start of the runway, with wreckage spread about another {{convert|328|ft|m}}.<ref name=CNN16Aug2010JetSplitsApart/> The aircraft skidded along the runway, fracturing the landing gear and ripping one engine from the wings.<ref name=AP17Aug2010130Survive/> The aircraft's nose and first eight rows of seating came to rest on the runway pointing in a different direction to the rest of the wreckage.<ref name=CNN16Aug2010JetSplitsApart/> Airport fire crews quickly doused a small fire that had started on a wing.<ref name=AP17Aug2010130Survive/> As a result of the accident, the Comit\u00e9 Regional de Prevenci\u00f3n y Atenci\u00f3n de Desastres was mobilized.<ref name=Eltiempo/>\n\n== Aircraft ==\nThe aircraft involved was a [[Boeing 737-700|Boeing 737-73V]],<ref group=Notes>The aircraft was a Boeing 737-700 model; Boeing assigns a unique code for each company that buys one of its aircraft, which is applied as an [[infix]] to the model number at the time the aircraft is built, hence \"737-73V\".</ref> registration HK-4682, with serial number (MSN) 32416, construction number 1270.<ref name=Airfleets/> The aircraft was built in 2003,<ref name=Airfleets/> and was first delivered to [[EasyJet]] registered as G-EZJU. It was then sold to AIRES in March 2010.<ref name=Airfleets/> Investigators said the day after the crash that the aircraft's maintenance log was up to date.<ref name=AP17Aug2010130Survive/>\n\n== Passengers and crew ==\n[[File:Seatmap of Aires 8250 (en).svg|thumbnail|right|Seat plan]]\nThere were contradictory reports as to how many people were aboard the aircraft.<ref name=CNN16Aug2010JetSplitsApart/> Reports range from 121 passengers and 6 crew members,<ref name=Reuters16Aug2010CrashesDuringStorm/> 131 passengers and crew,<ref name=BBC16Aug2010PlaneBreaks/> and at least 127 people aboard.<ref name=CNN16Aug2010JetSplitsApart/> The report of 131 people was further broken down as 121 adult passengers and four minors.<ref name=CNN16Aug2010JetSplitsApart/> Reports the day after the accident, settled on 131 people aboard: 125 passengers and 6 crew.<ref name=AP17Aug2010130Survive/><ref name=ABCNews17Aug2010InsideMiracle/><ref name=BBCNews17Aug2010AirCrashMiracle/><ref name=Yahoo17Aug2010WomanDies/>\n\nOne early report stated that 114 people were injured in the crash, and that of 99 passengers taken to the Amor de Patria Hospital on San Andr\u00e9s, only 4 had suffered major injuries.<ref name=BBC16Aug2010PlaneBreaks/> Reports a day later settled on a figure of 119 people being taken to local hospitals, mostly with minor injuries.<ref name=AP17Aug2010130Survive/><ref name=Yahoo17Aug2010WomanDies/> Thirteen survivors, including four with serious injuries, were flown to Bogota for treatment.<ref name=AP17Aug2010130Survive/>\n\nInitial reports indicated one fatality, an elderly lady dying of a heart attack.<ref>https://www.nytimes.com/2010/08/17/world/americas/17colombia.html</ref> The final fatality count was two. Autopsy revealed that a 68-year-old woman suffered a ruptured aorta and ruptured liver.<ref name=AviationHerald /> She died on the way to the hospital.<ref name=Reuters16Aug2010CrashesDuringStorm/><ref name=BBC16Aug2010PlaneBreaks/> The second fatality was a girl;<ref>\"[http://www.aires.aero/comunicado_06.html Comunicado de Prensa 06] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100909003235/http://www.aires.aero/comunicado_06.html |date=9 September 2010 }}.\" AIRES. Retrieved on 15 September 2010.</ref> she sustained substantial brain damage{{citation needed|date=September 2010}} and died 16 days after the accident.<ref>https://www.elpais.com.co/colombia/companeras-de-colegio-dieron-el-ultimo-adios-a-maria-camila-angarita.html</ref>\n\nOne report stated that the passenger list included six Americans, five Mexicans, four Brazilians, four Ecuadorians and two Germans, the rest being Colombians.<ref name=CNN16Aug2010JetSplitsApart/> Another report stated there were three Americans aboard.<ref name=Caracol/> A later report put the number of non-Colombians aboard as 'at least 16'.<ref name=BBCNews17Aug2010AirCrashMiracle/>\n\n== Investigation ==\nColombia's civil aviation authority, [[Special Administrative Unit of Civil Aeronautics]], and the [[Colombian Air Force]] opened an investigation into the accident.<ref name=Eltiempo/> The airport was closed as investigators examined the wreckage.<ref name=Reuters16Aug2010CrashesDuringStorm/> The closure was expected to last until 06:00 on 17 August.<ref name=Eltiempo/>\n\nThe aircraft reportedly crashed in bad weather, while a storm was reported in the area, but not at the airport.<ref name=CNN16Aug2010JetSplitsApart/> The [[METAR]] (aviation routine weather observation message) report in force at the time of the accident indicated that the wind was from the east north east at {{convert|6|kn|km/h mph|abbr=}}, visibility was good and that the runway was wet.<ref group=Notes>Raw data from the [[METAR]] report were: SKSP 160500Z 07006KT 9999 FEW016 SCT200 29/26 A2990=Translated: Gustavo Rojas Pinilla International Airport date: 16th day of the month, time: 0500 zulu/UTC, wind: 070\u00b0 at 6 kt, visibility: 10&nbsp;km or more, few clouds at 1600&nbsp;ft., scattered clouds at 20000&nbsp;ft., temperature 29&nbsp;\u00b0C, dew point 26&nbsp;\u00b0C, altimeter setting (pressure) 29.90 inHg.</ref><ref name=AviationHerald /> The aircraft \"landed in the middle of an intense electrical storm\" according to Colonel Barrero.<ref name=Reuters16Aug2010CrashesDuringStorm/>\n\nPassenger accounts the day after the crash detailed how the approach appeared to have been going normally, with the flight attendants having made the passengers ready for landing, when the crash occurred suddenly and without warning.<ref name=AP17Aug2010130Survive/><ref name=ABCNews17Aug2010InsideMiracle/><ref name=BBCNews17Aug2010AirCrashMiracle/> The pilot did not report an emergency to the tower.<ref name=Yahoo17Aug2010WomanDies/> There were conflicting reports over what caused the crash, suggesting that the landing was disrupted after the aircraft was hit by a [[downdraft]], or struck by [[lightning]].<ref name=CNN16Aug2010JetSplitsApart/> The pilot said that the aircraft was struck by lightning. Officials refused to comment on the reports of a lightning strike,<ref name=BBC16Aug2010PlaneBreaks/><ref name=CNN16Aug2010JetSplitsApart/><ref name=Eltiempo/> although subsequent research proved that{{specify|date=December 2018}} was not true. No aircraft has had an accident caused by lightning [[LANSA Flight 508|since 1971]]. The airport was not fitted with equipment such as a Doppler radar, used to detect wind shear.<ref name=AP17Aug2010130Survive/>\n\nBoth the [[flight recorder|flight data and cockpit voice recorders]] were recovered from the wreckage.<ref name=AP17Aug2010130Survive/> Based on the pattern of wreckage, investigators concluded that the aircraft had broken up on impact and not while in the air.<ref name=AP17Aug2010130Survive/>\n\nThe U.S. [[National Transportation Safety Board]] sent a team to support the Colombian-led investigation as representatives of the manufacturer's state.<ref>{{cite press release |url=http://www.ntsb.gov/Pressrel/2010/100816c.html |title=NTSB sending team to assist government of Colombia with today's 737 accident |date=16 August 2010 |publisher=[[National Transportation Safety Board]] }}</ref>\n\nAlmost one year after the accident, on 15 July 2011, the Security Council of Aeron\u00e1utica Civil concluded that the cause of the accident was the execution of the final approach below the glide path, due to an error of judgment by the crew who believed they were much higher. This is typical of a \"black hole\" illusion, which is experienced during a night approach to a low contrast runway environment surrounded by bright lights, aggravated by heavy rain.<ref name=\"Final report\"/> Aerona\u00fatica Civil recommended retraining of the crew. Although the accident was caused by human error, Aerona\u00fatica representative Colonel Carlos Silva reminded that the purpose of the investigation was not to apportion blame but to prevent aircraft accidents that may occur in the future.\n<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.eltiempo.com/colombia/otraszonas/ARTICULO-WEB-NEW_NOTA_INTERIOR-9916084.html|title=Error del piloto y mal tiempo, causas del accidente de avi\u00f3n de Aires|date=15 July 2011|work=[[El Tiempo (Colombia)|El Tiempo]]|accessdate=19 January 2013|language=Spanish|trans-title=Pilot error and bad weather, causes of the plane crash in Aires}}</ref>\n\n==Notes==\n{{reflist|group=Notes}}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|refs=\n\n<ref name=AviationHerald>{{cite web |url=http://www.avherald.com/h?article=42fb63a9&opt=0 | title=Accident: Aires B737 at San Andres Island on 16 Aug 2010, landed short of runway and broke up |accessdate=19 August 2010 |date=16 August 2010 |work=Aviation Herald}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=Airfleets>{{cite web|url=http://www.airfleets.net/ficheapp/plane-b737ng-32416.htm |title=Boeing 737 Next Gen \u2013 MSN 32416  |publisher=Airfleets |accessdate=20 April 2011}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=Reuters16Aug2010CrashesDuringStorm>{{cite news\n|url=https://af.reuters.com/article/worldNews/idAFTRE67F2AI20100816\n|title=Colombian airliner crashes during storm leaving one dead\n|publisher=Reuters\n|date=16 August 2010\n|accessdate=16 August 2010\n| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20100818183912/https://af.reuters.com/article/worldNews/idAFTRE67F2AI20100816| archivedate= 18 August 2010 | url-status= live}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=Eltiempo>{{cite web\n |url         = http://www.eltiempo.com/colombia/caribe/accidente-de-avion-en-san-andres_7866340-1\n |title       = Ministro de Transporte descart\u00f3 fallas t\u00e9cnicas de la aeronave que se accident\u00f3 en San Andr\u00e9s\n |publisher   = El Tiempo\n |language    = Spanish\n |accessdate  = 16 August 2010\n |url-status     = dead\n |archiveurl  = https://web.archive.org/web/20120928084901/http://www.eltiempo.com/colombia/caribe/accidente-de-avion-en-san-andres_7866340-1\n |archivedate = 28 September 2012\n |df          = dmy-all\n}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=Caracol>{{cite web\n|url=http://www.caracol.com.co/nota.aspx?id=1341509\n|title=Ministro de Transporte atribuy\u00f3 al clima el accidente a\u00e9reo en San Andr\u00e9s |publisher=Caracol\n|language=Spanish\n|accessdate=16 August 2010\n}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=CNN16Aug2010JetSplitsApart>{{cite news\n|url=http://edition.cnn.com/2010/WORLD/americas/08/16/colombia.plane.fatality/index.html\n|title=Jet breaks apart during landing in Colombia\n|publisher=CNN\n|date=16 August 2010\n|accessdate=16 August 2010\n| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20100818164414/http://edition.cnn.com/2010/WORLD/americas/08/16/colombia.plane.fatality/index.html| archivedate= 18 August 2010 | url-status= live}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=BBC16Aug2010PlaneBreaks>{{cite news\n|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-latin-america-10988966\n|title=Colombia plane breaks into pieces after crash\n|publisher=BBC News\n|date=16 August 2010\n|accessdate=16 August 2010\n| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20100816190031/http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-latin-america-10988966| archivedate= 16 August 2010 | url-status= live}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=RCN16Aug2010>{{cite web\n |url=http://www.rcnradio.com/noticias/nacional/16-08-10/gobierno-no-descarta-que-un-rayo-causar-el-accidente-reo\n |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110715161216/http://www.rcnradio.com/noticias/nacional/16-08-10/gobierno-no-descarta-que-un-rayo-causar-el-accidente-reo\n |url-status=dead\n |archive-date=15 July 2011\n |title=Gobierno no descarta que un rayo causar\u00e1 el accidente a\u00e9reo \n |publisher=RCN Radio \n |language=Spanish \n |date=16 August 2010 \n |accessdate=16 August 2010 \n}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=Yahoo17Aug2010WomanDies>{{cite news\n |url=https://news.yahoo.com/s/ap/20100816/ap_on_re_la_am_ca/lt_colombia_plane_crash \n |title='Miracle' in Colombia crash: Woman dies, 130 live \n |publisher=Yahoo \n |date=17 August 2010 \n |accessdate=17 August 2010 \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100816171706/http://news.yahoo.com/s/ap/20100816/ap_on_re_la_am_ca/lt_colombia_plane_crash \n |archivedate=16 August 2010 \n |url-status=dead \n  \n}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=AP17Aug2010130Survive>{{cite news\n|url=https://www.google.com/hostednews/ap/article/ALeqM5gw3-tyohDhSGDplj8TPrYOq3ojSwD9HLAFFG0\n|title=130 survive 'miracle' plane crash in Colombia\n|agency=Associated Press\n|date=17 August 2010\n|accessdate=17 August 2010\n| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20100820080305/https://www.google.com/hostednews/ap/article/ALeqM5gw3-tyohDhSGDplj8TPrYOq3ojSwD9HLAFFG0| archivedate= 20 August 2010 | url-status= live}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=ABCNews17Aug2010InsideMiracle>{{cite news\n|url=http://abcnews.go.com/International/colombian-miracle-plane-crash-inside-story-passengers-survival/story?id=11416690&page=2\n|title=Colombian 'Miracle' Plane Crash: Inside the Story of Survival\n|publisher=ABC News\n|date=17 August 2010\n|accessdate=17 August 2010\n| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20100821091502/http://abcnews.go.com/International/colombian-miracle-plane-crash-inside-story-passengers-survival/story?id=11416690&page=2| archivedate= 21 August 2010 | url-status= live}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=BBCNews17Aug2010AirCrashMiracle>{{cite news\n|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-latin-america-10998821\n|title=Air crash 'miracle' for Colombia as plane breaks up\n|publisher=BBC News\n|date=17 August 2010\n|accessdate=17 August 2010\n| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20100817194244/http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-latin-america-10998821| archivedate= 17 August 2010 | url-status= live}}</ref>\n\n}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{ASN accident|20100816-0}}\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20110722140135/http://www.aires.aero/comunicado.html Para informaci\u00f3n del vuelo 8250] \u2013 AIRES {{in lang|es}} (Archive)\n* [[Special Administrative Unit of Civil Aeronautics]] [http://www.aerocivil.gov.co/AAeronautica/InvAccidentes/LAccidentes/Accidentes/FINAL%20HK4682%20-%20part%20I.pdf Final report] ([https://www.webcitation.org/6S5Vv36Xv?url=http://www.aerocivil.gov.co/AAeronautica/InvAccidentes/LAccidentes/Accidentes/FINAL%20HK4682%20-%20part%20I.pdf Archive])\n* [http://www.radiosantafe.com/2010/08/16/lista-oficial-de-ocupantes-del-avion-8250-de-aires/ Passenger list] {{in lang|es}}\n\n{{Aviation accidents and incidents in Colombia}}\n{{Aviation accidents and incidents in 2010}}\n{{Portal bar|Aviation|Colombia}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Aires Flight 8250}}\n[[Category:2010 in Colombia]]\n[[Category:Aviation accidents and incidents in Colombia]]\n[[Category:Accidents and incidents involving the Boeing 737 Next Generation]]\n[[Category:Aviation accidents and incidents in 2010]]\n[[Category:Archipelago of San Andr\u00e9s, Providencia and Santa Catalina]]\n[[Category:August 2010 events in South America]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2019}}\n{{Infobox aircraft occurrence\n| image = AIRES-737-700.JPG\n| image_upright = \n| alt = \n| caption = HK-4682, the aircraft involved, seen at [[Bogot\u00e1 Airport]] five months before the crash\n| occurrence_type = Accident\n| date = {{Start date|2010|08|16|df=y}}\n| summary = [[Controlled flight into terrain | Runway undershoot]] due to [[pilot error]], aggravated by the [[Sensory_illusions_in_aviation#Black-hole_approach|black hole approach illusion]].<ref>''[[Mayday]]''. Season 20 Episode 5, \"Runway Breakup\".</ref>\n| site = [[Gustavo Rojas Pinilla International Airport]], [[San Andr\u00e9s, San Andr\u00e9s y Providencia|San Andr\u00e9s]], Colombia\n| coordinates = {{coord|12|34|45|N|81|43|10|W|source:kolossus-ptwiki_type:event|display=inline,title}}\n| aircraft_type = [[Boeing 737-700|Boeing 737-73V]]\n| aircraft_name = \n| operator = [[AIRES]]\n| IATA = \n| ICAO = ARE8250\n| callsign = \n| tail_number = HK-4682\n| origin = [[El Dorado International Airport]], [[Bogot\u00e1]], Colombia\n| destination = [[Gustavo Rojas Pinilla International Airport]], [[San Andr\u00e9s (island)|San Andr\u00e9s]], Colombia\n| occupants = 131\n| passengers = 125\n| crew = 6\n| fatalities= 2\n| injuries = 129\n| survivors = 129\n}}\n\n'''AIRES Flight 8250''' was a domestic scheduled passenger flight that on 16 August 2010 crashed on landing at night in poor weather on the Colombian island of [[San Andr\u00e9s (island)|San Andr\u00e9s]], killing 2 of the 131 people on board. The aircraft, an [[AIRES]]-operated [[Boeing 737-700]], was arriving from the Colombian capital [[Bogot\u00e1]] when it heavily touched down short of the runway, breaking up in three sections.\n\nThe official investigation concluded that the crash was caused by the misjudgement by the crew of the aircraft's altitude during the last phase of the approach.<ref name=\"Final report\">{{cite report |title=Accidente ocurrido el d\u00eda 16 de Agosto de 2010 a  la aeronave Boeing 737-700, Matr\u00edcula HK-4682 en el Aeropuerto Internacional Gustavo Rojas Pinilla de la Isla de San Andr\u00e9s - Colombia |url=http://reports.aviation-safety.net/2010/20100816-0_B737_HK-4682.pdf |accessdate=22 September 2019 |publisher=[[UAEAC]]}}</ref>\n\n== History of the flight ==\nFlight 8250 was operated by the local, privately owned Colombian airline [[AIRES]].<ref name=Reuters16Aug2010CrashesDuringStorm/><ref name=BBC16Aug2010PlaneBreaks/> The aircraft was on a flight from Bogot\u00e1 to the Colombian island of [[San Andr\u00e9s (island)|San Andr\u00e9s]], in the [[Caribbean]].<ref name=BBC16Aug2010PlaneBreaks/> A popular tourist destination, San Andres Island is about {{convert|190|km|mi nmi|abbr=}} east of the Nicaraguan coast.<ref name=BBC16Aug2010PlaneBreaks/>\n\nThe flight took off from Bogot\u00e1's [[El Dorado International Airport]] at 00:07 en route to [[Gustavo Rojas Pinilla International Airport]] with 125 passengers and six crew. [[pilot in command|Captain]] Wilson Gutierrez was the pilot flying (PF) while [[first officer (aeronautics)|First Officer]] Camilo Pineyros Rodriguez was pilot monitoring (PM).<ref name=RCN16Aug2010/>\n\n=== Accident ===\nThe crash occurred as the aircraft landed at San Andr\u00e9s at 1:49&nbsp;am local Western Caribbean Time ([[UTC\u221205:00]]).<ref name=BBC16Aug2010PlaneBreaks/><ref name=CNN16Aug2010JetSplitsApart/> The Boeing 737 broke up into three main sections.<ref name=AviationHerald/> The impact occurred about {{convert|260|ft|m|-1}} before the start of the runway, with wreckage spread about another {{convert|328|ft|m}}.<ref name=CNN16Aug2010JetSplitsApart/> The aircraft skidded along the runway, fracturing the landing gear and ripping one engine from the wings.<ref name=AP17Aug2010130Survive/> The aircraft's nose and first eight rows of seating came to rest on the runway pointing in a different direction to the rest of the wreckage.<ref name=CNN16Aug2010JetSplitsApart/> Airport fire crews quickly doused a small fire that had started on a wing.<ref name=AP17Aug2010130Survive/> As a result of the accident, the Comit\u00e9 Regional de Prevenci\u00f3n y Atenci\u00f3n de Desastres was mobilized.<ref name=Eltiempo/>\n\n== Aircraft ==\nThe aircraft involved was a [[Boeing 737-700|Boeing 737-73V]],<ref group=Notes>The aircraft was a Boeing 737-700 model; Boeing assigns a unique code for each company that buys one of its aircraft, which is applied as an [[infix]] to the model number at the time the aircraft is built, hence \"737-73V\".</ref> registration HK-4682, with serial number (MSN) 32416, construction number 1270.<ref name=Airfleets/> The aircraft was built in 2003,<ref name=Airfleets/> and was first delivered to [[EasyJet]] registered as G-EZJU. It was then sold to AIRES in March 2010.<ref name=Airfleets/> Investigators said the day after the crash that the aircraft's maintenance log was up to date.<ref name=AP17Aug2010130Survive/>\n\n== Passengers and crew ==\n[[File:Seatmap of Aires 8250 (en).svg|thumbnail|right|Seat plan]]\nThere were contradictory reports as to how many people were aboard the aircraft.<ref name=CNN16Aug2010JetSplitsApart/> Reports range from 121 passengers and 6 crew members,<ref name=Reuters16Aug2010CrashesDuringStorm/> 131 passengers and crew,<ref name=BBC16Aug2010PlaneBreaks/> and at least 127 people aboard.<ref name=CNN16Aug2010JetSplitsApart/> The report of 131 people was further broken down as 121 adult passengers and four minors.<ref name=CNN16Aug2010JetSplitsApart/> Reports the day after the accident, settled on 131 people aboard: 125 passengers and 6 crew.<ref name=AP17Aug2010130Survive/><ref name=ABCNews17Aug2010InsideMiracle/><ref name=BBCNews17Aug2010AirCrashMiracle/><ref name=Yahoo17Aug2010WomanDies/>\n\nOne early report stated that 114 people were injured in the crash, and that of 99 passengers taken to the Amor de Patria Hospital on San Andr\u00e9s, only 4 had suffered major injuries.<ref name=BBC16Aug2010PlaneBreaks/> Reports a day later settled on a figure of 119 people being taken to local hospitals, mostly with minor injuries.<ref name=AP17Aug2010130Survive/><ref name=Yahoo17Aug2010WomanDies/> Thirteen survivors, including four with serious injuries, were flown to Bogota for treatment.<ref name=AP17Aug2010130Survive/>\n\nInitial reports indicated one fatality, an elderly lady dying of a heart attack.<ref>https://www.nytimes.com/2010/08/17/world/americas/17colombia.html</ref> The final fatality count was two. Autopsy revealed that a 68-year-old woman suffered a ruptured aorta and ruptured liver.<ref name=AviationHerald /> She died on the way to the hospital.<ref name=Reuters16Aug2010CrashesDuringStorm/><ref name=BBC16Aug2010PlaneBreaks/> The second fatality was a girl;<ref>\"[http://www.aires.aero/comunicado_06.html Comunicado de Prensa 06] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100909003235/http://www.aires.aero/comunicado_06.html |date=9 September 2010 }}.\" AIRES. Retrieved on 15 September 2010.</ref> she sustained substantial brain damage{{citation needed|date=September 2010}} and died 16 days after the accident.<ref>https://www.elpais.com.co/colombia/companeras-de-colegio-dieron-el-ultimo-adios-a-maria-camila-angarita.html</ref>\n\nOne report stated that the passenger list included six Americans, five Mexicans, four Brazilians, four Ecuadorians and two Germans, the rest being Colombians.<ref name=CNN16Aug2010JetSplitsApart/> Another report stated there were three Americans aboard.<ref name=Caracol/> A later report put the number of non-Colombians aboard as 'at least 16'.<ref name=BBCNews17Aug2010AirCrashMiracle/>\n\n== Investigation ==\nColombia's civil aviation authority, [[Special Administrative Unit of Civil Aeronautics]], and the [[Colombian Air Force]] opened an investigation into the accident.<ref name=Eltiempo/> The airport was closed as investigators examined the wreckage.<ref name=Reuters16Aug2010CrashesDuringStorm/> The closure was expected to last until 06:00 on 17 August.<ref name=Eltiempo/>\n\nThe aircraft reportedly crashed in bad weather, while a storm was reported in the area, but not at the airport.<ref name=CNN16Aug2010JetSplitsApart/> The [[METAR]] (aviation routine weather observation message) report in force at the time of the accident indicated that the wind was from the east north east at {{convert|6|kn|km/h mph|abbr=}}, visibility was good and that the runway was wet.<ref group=Notes>Raw data from the [[METAR]] report were: SKSP 160500Z 07006KT 9999 FEW016 SCT200 29/26 A2990=Translated: Gustavo Rojas Pinilla International Airport date: 16th day of the month, time: 0500 zulu/UTC, wind: 070\u00b0 at 6 kt, visibility: 10&nbsp;km or more, few clouds at 1600&nbsp;ft., scattered clouds at 20000&nbsp;ft., temperature 29&nbsp;\u00b0C, dew point 26&nbsp;\u00b0C, altimeter setting (pressure) 29.90 inHg.</ref><ref name=AviationHerald /> The aircraft \"landed in the middle of an intense electrical storm\" according to Colonel Barrero.<ref name=Reuters16Aug2010CrashesDuringStorm/>\n\nPassenger accounts the day after the crash detailed how the approach appeared to have been going normally, with the flight attendants having made the passengers ready for landing, when the crash occurred suddenly and without warning.<ref name=AP17Aug2010130Survive/><ref name=ABCNews17Aug2010InsideMiracle/><ref name=BBCNews17Aug2010AirCrashMiracle/> The pilot did not report an emergency to the tower.<ref name=Yahoo17Aug2010WomanDies/> There were conflicting reports over what caused the crash, suggesting that the landing was disrupted after the aircraft was hit by a [[downdraft]], or struck by [[lightning]].<ref name=CNN16Aug2010JetSplitsApart/> The pilot said that the aircraft was struck by lightning. Officials refused to comment on the reports of a lightning strike,<ref name=BBC16Aug2010PlaneBreaks/><ref name=CNN16Aug2010JetSplitsApart/><ref name=Eltiempo/> although subsequent research proved that{{specify|date=December 2018}} was not true. No aircraft has had an accident caused by lightning [[LANSA Flight 508|since 1971]]. The airport was not fitted with equipment such as a Doppler radar, used to detect wind shear.<ref name=AP17Aug2010130Survive/>\n\nBoth the [[flight recorder|flight data and cockpit voice recorders]] were recovered from the wreckage.<ref name=AP17Aug2010130Survive/> Based on the pattern of wreckage, investigators concluded that the aircraft had broken up on impact and not while in the air.<ref name=AP17Aug2010130Survive/>\n\nThe U.S. [[National Transportation Safety Board]] sent a team to support the Colombian-led investigation as representatives of the manufacturer's state.<ref>{{cite press release |url=http://www.ntsb.gov/Pressrel/2010/100816c.html |title=NTSB sending team to assist government of Colombia with today's 737 accident |date=16 August 2010 |publisher=[[National Transportation Safety Board]] }}</ref>\n\nAlmost one year after the accident, on 15 July 2011, the Security Council of Aeron\u00e1utica Civil concluded that the cause of the accident was the execution of the final approach below the glide path, due to an error of judgment by the crew who believed they were much higher. This is typical of a \"black hole\" illusion, which is experienced during a night approach to a low contrast runway environment surrounded by bright lights, aggravated by heavy rain.<ref name=\"Final report\"/> Aerona\u00fatica Civil recommended retraining of the crew. Although the accident was caused by human error, Aerona\u00fatica representative Colonel Carlos Silva reminded that the purpose of the investigation was not to apportion blame but to prevent aircraft accidents that may occur in the future.\n<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.eltiempo.com/colombia/otraszonas/ARTICULO-WEB-NEW_NOTA_INTERIOR-9916084.html|title=Error del piloto y mal tiempo, causas del accidente de avi\u00f3n de Aires|date=15 July 2011|work=[[El Tiempo (Colombia)|El Tiempo]]|accessdate=19 January 2013|language=Spanish|trans-title=Pilot error and bad weather, causes of the plane crash in Aires}}</ref>\n\n==Notes==\n{{reflist|group=Notes}}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|refs=\n\n<ref name=AviationHerald>{{cite web |url=http://www.avherald.com/h?article=42fb63a9&opt=0 | title=Accident: Aires B737 at San Andres Island on 16 Aug 2010, landed short of runway and broke up |accessdate=19 August 2010 |date=16 August 2010 |work=Aviation Herald}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=Airfleets>{{cite web|url=http://www.airfleets.net/ficheapp/plane-b737ng-32416.htm |title=Boeing 737 Next Gen \u2013 MSN 32416  |publisher=Airfleets |accessdate=20 April 2011}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=Reuters16Aug2010CrashesDuringStorm>{{cite news\n|url=https://af.reuters.com/article/worldNews/idAFTRE67F2AI20100816\n|title=Colombian airliner crashes during storm leaving one dead\n|publisher=Reuters\n|date=16 August 2010\n|accessdate=16 August 2010\n| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20100818183912/https://af.reuters.com/article/worldNews/idAFTRE67F2AI20100816| archivedate= 18 August 2010 | url-status= live}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=Eltiempo>{{cite web\n |url         = http://www.eltiempo.com/colombia/caribe/accidente-de-avion-en-san-andres_7866340-1\n |title       = Ministro de Transporte descart\u00f3 fallas t\u00e9cnicas de la aeronave que se accident\u00f3 en San Andr\u00e9s\n |publisher   = El Tiempo\n |language    = Spanish\n |accessdate  = 16 August 2010\n |url-status     = dead\n |archiveurl  