n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n!2015-16\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n!2016-17\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n!2017-18\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n|}\n\n===Key===\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-4}}\n* P = Played\n* W = Games won\n* D = Games drawn\n* L = Games lost\n* F = Goals for\n* A = Goals against\n* Pts = Points\n* Pos = Final position\n{{col-4}}\n* TJC = [[Takht Jamshid Cup]]\n* TFL = [[Tehran Province league|Tehran Football League]]\n* TFL2 = [[Tehran Province league|Tehran Football League's 2nd Div.]]\n* Div 3 = [[Iran Football's 3rd Division|3rd Division]]\n\n{{col-end}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|bgcolor=gold|<small>Champions</small>\n|bgcolor=silver|<small>Runners-up</small>\n|}\n\n==Founder and manager==\n* {{flagicon|Iran}} Dr. [[Abbas Ekrami]] (1942\u20131970)\n\n==Managers==\n* {{flagicon|Iran}} [[Shapoor Sarhadi]]\n* {{flagicon|Iran}} [[Amirhoshang Nikkhah Baharami]]\n* {{flagicon|Iran}} [[Jafar Kashani]]\n* {{flagicon|Iran}} [[Amirhoshang Nikkhah Bahrami]]\n\n==World Cup players<ref>http://www.planetworldcup.com/CUPS/1978/squad_irn78.html</ref>==\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-3}}\n'''{{flagicon|Argentina}} [[1978 FIFA World Cup]]\n* {{flagicon|Iran}} [[Nasrollah Abdollahi]]\n* {{flagicon|Iran}} [[Nasser Hejazi]]\n* {{flagicon|Iran}} [[Ebrahim Ghasempour]]\n* {{flagicon|Iran}} [[Hamid-Majid Tajmuri]]\n* {{flagicon|Iran}} [[Majid Bishkar]]\n{{col-end}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==See also==\n* [[Hazfi Cup]]\n* [[2011\u201312 Iran Football's 3rd Division|Iran Football's 3rd Division 2011\u201312]]\n\n===Official===\n* {{in lang|fa}} [http://www.shahinfc.net/ Official club website]\n\n{{Football in Iran}}\n\n[[Category:Football clubs in Iran]]\n[[Category:Defunct football clubs in Iran]]\n[[Category:Association football clubs established in 1942]]\n[[Category:Sport in Tehran]]\n[[Category:1942 establishments in Iran]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox football club\n| clubname    = Shahin|\n| image       = <!-- Commented out: [[File:ShahinClub logo.png|230px]] -->\n| fullname    = Shahin Tehran Football Club\n| nickname    =\n| founded     = 1942, as ''Shahin ''; 75 years ago<br />1973, as ''Shabaz ''; 44 years ago<br />1979, as ''Shahin ''; 38 years ago\n| ground      = [[Shahid Shiroudi Stadium]]<br>[[Tehran]], [[Iran]]\n| capacity    = 30,000\n| chairman    =\n| manager     =\n| league      = [[Tehran Province league]]\n| season      = 2013\u201314\n| position    = Tehran Province league, 8th\n| pattern_la1 =_blackborder| pattern_b1=_vneckblack| pattern_ra1=_blackborder| pattern_so1=_blacktop\n| leftarm1    =FFFFFF| body1=FFFFFF| rightarm1=FFFFFF| shorts1=000000| socks1=FFFFFF\n| pattern_la2 =_shoulder_stripes_white_stripes_alt|pattern_b2=_whitecollar|pattern_ra2=_shoulder_stripes_white_stripes_alt| pattern_so2=_color_3_stripes_black|pattern_sh=_adidasonwhite|leftarm2=000000|body2=000000|rightarm2=000000|shorts2=FFFFFF|socks2=000000|\n}}\n\n'''Shahin Tehran Football Club''' ({{lang-fa|\u0628\u0627\u0634\u06af\u0627\u0647 \u0641\u0648\u062a\u0628\u0627\u0644 \u0634\u0627\u0647\u06cc\u0646 \u062a\u0647\u0631\u0627\u0646|Sh\u0101h\u012bn}} meaning ''[[Falcon]]'') also spelled '''Shaahin''' or '''Shaheen''', from 1973 to 1979 known as '''Shahbaz''' ({{lang-fa|\u0634\u0647\u0628\u0627\u0632|Shahb\u0101z}}, meaning ''[[Shahbaz (bird)|Shahbaz]]''),\nis an [[Iran]]ian [[Football (soccer)|football]] club based in [[Tehran]], [[Iran]]. Shahin A.C. is located at East of Tehran in the Narmak neighborhood (Golestan Street). Shahin was the most popular clubs in Iran before the 1960s and it had a rivalry with [[Taj SC|Taj Tehran]]. Their match was the most important derby of Iran at the time. Shahin F.C. was dissolved in 1967 for political reasons. Shahin was revived again after the [[Iranian Revolution]] in 1979. Due to the [[Iran\u2013Iraq War]], The national league was not held during the 1980s, however, Shahin was one of the strongest teams in the provincial league of Tehran.\n\nThey currently compete in the Tehran provincial league.\n\n==History==\n[[File:Amjadieh Stadium.jpg|thumb|right|[[Amjadieh Stadium]] home of Shahin F.C.]]\nIn June 1942, Dr. [[Abbas Ekrami]] opened the poetry book [[Hafez|Divan-e Hafez]] and saw the following line about Shahin (Falcon), after which he named the club Shahin,\n{{cquote|\n{{lang|fa|\u062f\u0631 \u0647\u0648\u0627 \u0686\u0646\u062f \u0645\u0639\u0644\u0642 \u0632\u0646\u06cc \u0648 \u062c\u0644\u0648\u0647 \u06a9\u0646\u06cc<br> \u0627\u06cc \u06a9\u0628\u0648\u062a\u0631 \u0646\u06af\u0631\u0627\u0646 \u0628\u0627\u0634 \u06a9\u0647 \u0634\u0627\u0647\u06cc\u0646 \u0622\u0645\u062f}}<br>\n''In the air, you will rotate a few times with glory;<br> oh pigeon, be worried, Falcon is on its way.''\n}}\n\nEkrami founded the club with help of some young students<ref>{{cite web\n|title = \u062a\u0627\u0631\u06cc\u062e\u0686\u0647 \u067e\u0631\u0633\u067e\u0648\u0644\u06cc\u0633 \u0627\u0632 \u0634\u0627\u0647\u06cc\u0646\n|url = http://www.aftabir.com/articles/view/sport/federation/c6c1206701610_perspolice_p1.php/%D8%AA%D8%A7%D8%B1%DB%8C%D8%AE%DA%86%D9%87-%D9%BE%D8%B1%D8%B3%D9%BE%D9%88%D9%84%DB%8C%D8%B3-%D8%A7%D8%B2-%D8%B4%D8%A7%D9%87%DB%8C%D9%86}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title =\u06af\u0631\u0627\u0645\u06cc \u0628\u0627\u062f \u06cc\u0627\u062f \u0648 \u062e\u0627\u0637\u0631\u0647 \u0628\u0646\u06cc\u0627\u0646\u06af\u0630\u0627\u0631 \u0645\u06a9\u062a\u0628 \u0634\u0627\u0647\u06cc\u0646|url =http://www.kanonshahin.ir/the-news/2445-1390-11-16-07-32-34.html|url-status =dead|archiveurl =https://archive.is/20130616024954/http://www.kanonshahin.ir/the-news/2445-1390-11-16-07-32-34.html|archivedate =2013-06-16}}</ref> under the motto:\n{{cquote|{{Lang|fa| \u0627\u0648\u0644 \u0627\u062e\u0644\u0627\u0642\u060c  \u062f\u0648\u0645 \u062f\u0631\u0633\u060c  \u0633\u0648\u0645 \u0648\u0631\u0632\u0634}} <br>''First ethics, second education, third sports.''<ref name=\"Ghermezeteh\">{{cite web\n|title= \u062a\u0627\u0631\u06cc\u062e\u0686\u0647 \u0628\u0627\u0634\u06af\u0627\u0647 \u0627\u0632 \u0634\u0627\u0647\u064a\u0646\n|url=http://ghermezeteh.com/joomla/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=12&Itemid=29\n|publisher=ghermezeteh.com\n}}</ref>}}\n\nShahin became a prominent club in Iran and formed other teams for its sub-clubs Oghab FC, Shahbaz FC, Darius FC, Simorgh FC, Atom FC, and Pirooz FC. The club also produced many famous Iranian players such as [[Masoud Boroumand]], [[Homayoun Behzadi]] and [[Mehrab Shahrokhi]].\n\n[[File:Shahinfc.jpg|thumb|220px|right|'''Shahin F.C. in mid 1960s'''<br><small>Many of the players shown in this photo went on to play for Persepolis.</small>]]\n\nShahin FC, without any doubt was the most popular football club in the history of Iranian football. Shahin produced many talented players like [[Parviz Dehdari]], [[Masoud Boroumand]], [[Homayoun Behzadi]], [[Jafar Kashani]], [[Hossein Kalani]], [[Hamid Shirzadegan]], and many more that played for [[Team Melli]]. These talents made Shahin popular in the 1960s but its very popularity was viewed as a threat by the [[IRIFF|Iran Football Federation]] and the ''Keihan Varzeshi'' newspaper (Iran's most important sports publication at the time).<ref name=\"enhelal\"/> The conflict between them became worse and on July 9, 1967, two days after Shahin's 3\u20130 win against [[Tehranjavan F.C.]], the Iran Sports Organization declared Shahin F.C. as dissolved.<ref name=\"enhelal\">{{cite web\n|title=40 \u0633\u0627\u0644 \u0628\u0639\u062f \u0627\u0632 \u0627\u0646\u062d\u0644\u0627\u0644 \u062a\u0627\u0631\u064a\u062e\u064a \u0634\u0627\u0647\u064a\u0646\n|url=http://www.etemaad.com/Released/86-04-14/225.htm|publisher= etemad.com\n|accessdate=2007-07-05|language=fa}}</ref> League attendance dropped and other clubs including [[Pas Tehran F.C.|Pas Tehran]], [[Rah Ahan F.C.|Rah Ahan]], and [[Oghab F.C.|Oghab]] tried to sign Shahin players.\n\nDespite the efforts to sign and disperse Shahin players to various clubs, Parviz Dehdari, newly appointed manager of [[Persepolis F.C.]], and Masoud Boroumand persuaded most Shahin players to join Persepolis and granted the popularity of Shahin to Persepolis.\n\n===Shahbaz Era===\nIn 1973 Shahin F.C. decided to come back but returned with the name of its former third team '''Shahbaz F.C.''' and participated in [[Takht Jamshid Cup]] professional soccer League. Shahbaz F.C. was leading the league in the [[1978\u201379 Takht Jamshid Cup|1978\u20131979]] season which was unfinished due to [[Iranian Revolution]] in 1979. After the revolution, the club reverted to its original name, \"Shahin\", and was among one of the top teams of in Iranian football during the 1980s.\n\nIn [[2009\u201310 Iran Football's 3rd Division|2009/10]] Shahin was competing in the third ranked [[Iran Football's 2nd Division|2nd Division]] successfully until the last stage, when they failed to be promoted to the Azadegan [[Iran Football's 1st Division|1st Division]]. In [[2010\u201311 Iran Football's 3rd Division|2010/11]] Shahin kept its place in the 3rd Division.\n\nIn [[2011\u201312 Iran Football's 3rd Division|2011/12]] Shahin finished last in its group and therefore is relegated to the provincial league for 2012/13.\n\n==Branches and affiliated clubs==\nShahin F.C. had several attached teams and branches under the name and license of Shahin F.C. in different cities of Iran, including '''[[Shahin Bushehr F.C.]]''' (est. 1942), '''[[Shahin Ahvaz F.C.]]''' (est. 1948) and '''Shahin Isfahan F.C.'''(est. 1953). In 1967 due to the political problems that arose in the Shahin F.C. organization, the other teams were forced to cease operations as well. Some had to deactivate for a period of time, while other teams renamed and continued under different names.\n\n'''[[Persepolis F.C.]]''' started the 1968 season with Parviz Dehdari as manager. Despite the efforts to sign and disperse Shahin players to various clubs, [[Parviz Dehdari]] and [[Masoud Boroumand]] transferred the popularity of Shahin to Persepolis F.C. by taking most Shahin Players to join Persepolis. Persepolis F.C. using four Shahin players, had a friendly match with ''Jam Abadan'', a respected team at the time. After the match the remainder of the Shahin players joined Persepolis. Although Shahin Tehran established in a new team under the name of Shahbaz, it was failed to get back its popularity again.\n\n'''Shahin Isfahan F.C.''' changed its name to '''[[Sepahan F.C.]]'''. The club is one of the representatives of [[Isfahan Province]] in [[Takht Jamshid Cup]] national league. The team now plays under the name of Foolad Mobarakeh Sepahan, and has been able to attain a respectable fan base in its hometown.\n\n'''[[Shahin Bushehr F.C.|Shahin Bushehr]]''' is one of the most popular clubs of Iran. After years of history and competing in different levels of the [[Iranian football league system]], including a 1994\u201395 appearance in the [[Iran Pro League|top division]] and several years in the second level, Shahin Bushehr was renamed '''Shahin Pars Jonoubi Bushehr''' in 2007 and promoted to [[Iran's Premier Football League|IPL]] in 2009. The club is now owned by ''Pars Special Economic Energy Zone'', based in [[Asalouyeh]], [[Bushehr Province]] and currently competes in the [[Iran Football's 2nd Division|2nd Division]] after being relegated from [[Azadegan League]] in 2013.\n\n'''[[Shahin Ahvaz F.C.]]''' was founded in 1948 and was one of Shahin Tehran F.C. branches at the time. The golden years of '''Shahin Ahvaz F.C.''' were in the 1980s when the team won its very first \"Hazfi cup\" after defeating Persepolis Tehran in the semi-finals and then [[Malavan F.C.|Malavan Anzali]] in the final game. This winning made them qualify to the Asian Club Championship. They currently compete in the Provincial Leagues.\n\n==Colours and crest==\nThe usual home kit includes a white shirt, black shorts, and white socks. The away kit of the club is commonly with a black background.{{clarify|date=May 2014}}\n\n==Achievements==\n\n===Takht Jamshid Cup===\n* '''Third place''': [[Takht Jamshid Cup 1976\u201377|1976/77]]\n* '''Leader''': [[Takht Jamshid Cup 1978\u201379|1978/79]] (in autumn 1978 the season was canceled due to the political uprisings, which ended with the [[Iranian Revolution]] in February 1979)\n\n===Tehran Football League===\n* '''Winner (3)''': 1951\u201352,1958\u201359,1965\u201366\n* '''Runner-up (8)''': 1948\u201349, 1949\u201350, 1947\u201348, 1949\u201350, 1961\u201362, 1963\u201364, 1985_86,1986_87\n\n===Tehran Hazfi Cup <small>(Record)</small>===\n* '''Winner (5)''': 1947\u201348, 1948\u201349, 1949\u201350, 1962\u201363, 1980\u201381\n* '''Runner-up (3)''': 1952\u201353, 1956\u201357, 1957\u201358\n\n===Espandi Cup===\n* '''Third place''': [[1979 Shahid Espandi Cup|1979]]\nCurrent Exuctive Director:Alireza Kushanfar\n\n==Season-by-season==\n\nThe table below chronicles the achievements of Shahin in various competitions since 1965.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center\"\n|-\n!rowspan=2|Season\n!colspan=9|League\n!rowspan=2|[[Hazfi Cup]]\n!rowspan=2|Notes\n!colspan=2|Leagues Top goalscorer\n!rowspan=2|Coach\n|-\n!Division\n!P\n!W\n!D\n!L\n!F\n!A\n!Pts\n!Pos\n!Name\n!Goals\n|-\n!1965\u201366\n|[[Tehran Province league|TFL]]\n|12\n|11\n|0\n|1\n|36\n|8\n|22\n|align=left bgcolor=gold|'''1st'''\n|align=left|\n|\n|align=left|\n|\n|[[Parviz Dehdari]]\n|-\n!1966\u201367\n|[[Tehran Province league|TFL]]\n|11\n|6\n|2\n|3\n|23\n|11\n|14\n|4th\n|align=left|\n|\n|align=left|\n|\n|[[Parviz Dehdari]]\n|-\n!1967\u201368\n|[[Tehran Province league|TFL]]\n|colspan=8|<small>''' Shahin dissolved'''\n|align=left|'''Not held'''\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n!1968\u201369\n|[[Tehran Province league|TFL]]\n|colspan=8|'''Absence'''\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n!1969\u201370\n|[[Tehran Province league|TFL]]\n|colspan=8|'''Absence'''\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n!1970\u201371\n|[[Tehran Province league|TFL]]\n|colspan=8|'''Absence'''\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n!1971\u201372\n