{"title_page": "Tanjiro Kamado", "text_new": "{{Infobox animanga character\n| name         = Tanjiro Kamado\n| series       = [[Demon Slayer: Kimetsu no Yaiba]]\n| creator      = Koyoharu Got\u014dge\n| image        = Tanjirou_manga.png\n| caption      = The original manga illustration of Tanjiro preparing to draw his sword.\n| first        = ''Demon Slayer: Kimetsu no Yaiba'' chapter 1: Cruelty (2016)\n| relatives    = Tanjuro Kamado (father, deceased) <br> Kie Kamado (mother, deceased) <br> [[List of Demon Slayer: Kimetsu no Yaiba characters#Nezuko Kamado|Nezuko Kamado]] (sister) <br> Takeo Kamado (brother, deceased) <br> Hanako Kamado (sister, deceased) <br> Shigeru Kamado (brother, deceased) <br> Rokuta Kamado (brother, deceased)\n| voiced by = [[Natsuki Hanae]], [[Satomi Sat\u014d]] (child)<ref name=\"stars\">{{cite web |url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2018-10-05/demon-slayer-kimetsu-no-yaiba-anime-stars-natsuki-hanae-akari-kito/.137769 |title=Demon Slayer: Kimetsu no Yaiba Anime Stars Natsuki Hanae, Akari Kit\u014d |last=Pineda |first=Rafael Antonio |date=October 5, 2018 |website=[[Anime News Network]] |accessdate=October 5, 2018 }}</ref><br/>Zach Aguilar,<ref name=\"English1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-10-09/demon-slayer-kimetsu-no-yaiba-anime-trailer-reveals-english-dub-cast/.152061|title=Demon Slayer: Kimetsu no Yaiba Anime's Trailer Reveals English Dub Cast|website=Anime News Network|access-date=2019-10-09}}</ref> Allegra Clark (child) (English)                                                                                         \n}}\n{{Nihongo|'''Tanjiro Kamado'''|\u7ac8\u9580 \u70ad\u6cbb\u90ce|Kamado Tanjir\u014d|lead=yes}} is a fictional character in Koyoharu Got\u014dge's [[manga]] ''[[Demon Slayer: Kimetsu no Yaiba]]''. Tanjiro is a teenager who goes on a quest to restore the humanity of his sister, [[Nezuko Kamado|Nezuko]], who was turned into a demon after his family was killed by Muzan Kibutsuji. After an encounter with [[Giyu Tomioka]], a demon slayer, Tanjiro is recruited by Giyu to also become a demon slayer to help his sister turn human again and avenge his family. Besides the ''Demon Slayer: Kimetsu no Yaiba'' [[anime]] adaptation, Tanjiro has also appeared in a [[light novel]] that acts as a prequel to the manga.\n \nKoyoharu Got\u014dge created Tanjiro following a suggestion from his editor of having a bright main character who would stand out in his dark narrative. His design influenced by [[Himura Kenshin]] from [[Nobuhiro Watsuki]]'s manga ''[[Rurouni Kenshin]]'' when deciding how andrognynous the character should look. In the anime series, Tanjiro is voiced by [[Natsuki Hanae]] in Japanese and Zach Aguilar in English. The character has been well received by manga and anime critics due to his caring nature and relationship with his sister, winning multiple awards based on his popularity.\n\n==Creation and design==\n[[File:NezukoTanjiroearlysketch.jpg|thumb|left|Early sketches of Nezuko and Tanjiro]]\nTanjiro Kamado originates from Koyoharu Got\u014dge's ideas involving a one-shot with Japanese motifs. Tatsuhiko Katayama, his editor, was worried about the one-shot being too dark for the young demographic and asked Got\u014dge if he could write another type of main character who would be \"brighter\".<ref name=\"creation\">{{cite web|url=https://mangaplus.shueisha.co.jp/web_pages/234/|title=The birth of \"Demon Slayer: Kimetsu no Yaiba\"|publisher=Shueisha|website=Manga Plus|accessdate=February 16, 2020}}</ref> Got\u014dge has cited issues in the making of the character due to the contrast he has with the dark narrative. For the release of the manga's seventh chapter, Got\u014dge drew a cover of Tanjiro wielding his sword while smiling. However, due to the constrating aesthetics the manga had. As a result, Got\u014dge discarded the drawing and instead drew a similar design with Tanjiro having a serious expression.<ref>{{cite book|title=Demon Slayer: Kimetsu no Yaiba|volume=2|publisher=Viz Media|isbn=978-1-9747-0053-0|year=2018|author=Got\u014dge, Koyoharu}}</ref>\n\nIn the initial design, Tanjiro did not have a scar or wear earrings, but in the end they felt these features really accentuated the character. In the making of the cast, Tanjiro had four supporting characters who would balance each other due to their different skills. The editor commented about Tanjiro, \"[He] is a type of male main character that you don't really see much. He's so kind. He has Nezuko, so he's coming from this position where he can't just say all demons are absolute evil. He's in the gray zone.\" Tanjiro's design was also influenced by Got\u014dge's editor: He suggested giving Tanjiro a facial scar in his forehead inspired by [[Himura Kenshin]] from [[Nobuhiro Watsuki]]'s manga ''[[Rurouni Kenshin]]'' while also giving him earrings in order to balance how androgynous he would look.<ref name=\"creation\"/>\n\nYuma Takahashi, the producer behind the adaptation of the manga said he enjoyed Tanjiro's role in the manga, making him engaged in reading the series. For how Tanjiro's Water Breathing was portrayed, [[Ufotable]] received inspiration from [[Katsushika Hokusai]]'s [[ukiyo-e]] style. The first fight scene between Tanjiro and Giyu was also carefully animated to give viewers an appealing choreography.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.crunchyroll.com/es-es/anime-feature/2019/08/16/yuma-takahashi-talks-about-producing-one-of-animes-biggest-hits?referrer=community_cr_twitter_news|title=Yuma Takahashi Talks About Producing One of Anime's Biggest Hits!|publisher=Crunchyroll|accessdate=February 16, 2020}}</ref> Tanjiro's water-based techniques were created using a mix between hand-drawn animation and CGI, while his battle against Rui was one of the most worked scenes in the making. Takahashi also said that Tanjiro is his most relatable character from the series due to how his constant hard work inspires him.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/feature/2019-08-28/interview-demon-slayer-producer-yuma-takahashi/.149177|title=Interview: Demon Slayer producer Yuma Takahashi|publisher=Anime News Network|accessdate=February 16, 2020}}</ref>\n\nWhen the anime series premiered in China, Tanjiro's design was sightly altered. Due to his piercings having Rising Sun style elements, it was feared it would offend the Mainland leading to brief retouches to them.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://kotaku.com/anime-demon-slayer-kimetsu-no-yaiba-changed-slightly-a-1833879190|title=Anime Demon Slayer: Kimetsu no Yaiba Changed Slightly In China As Not To Offend|publisher=Kotaku|accessdate=February 16, 2020}}</ref>\n\n=== Voice actors ===\nTanjiro has been voiced by [[Natsuki Hanae]] in Japanese. Hanae noted that multiple response to his career involved him portraying sad characters. However, in Tanjiro's case, he said Tanjiro is on the easy side because he says what he thinks, and is not the type that thinks one way and other things. Nezuko's actress, [[Akari Kit\u014d]], said Hanae is like a big brother to her at the studio, supportive and if there are parts she has difficulty recording, Hanae would stay and wait till she finishes even though his part has finished. Hanae said she also thinks of Kit\u014d as a younger sister. He also says it is easier for him to do his best when he is around people who he is friendly with.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://natalie.mu/comic/pp/kimetsu|title=\u300c\u9b3c\u6ec5\u306e\u5203\u300d\u3068\u306f\uff1f|publisher=Ntalie|accessdate=February 16, 2020}}</ref>\n\nEnglish voice actor Zach Aguilar was overjoyed when being given the role of voicing Tanjiro in the dub due to him being a fan of the series, as well as noting he was supported by multiple fans.<ref>{{cite tweet |author=Zach Aguilar|user=airzach\n|number=1182014282487042048 |date=October 9, 2019 |title=Incredibly honored by this - I\u2019m voicing Tanjiro for the English dub of Demon Slayer! Being a huge fan of the show, I\u2019m so excited to have been able to work on this with the team at @aniplexUSA and @BangZoom. Thank you to everyone for your support!|access-date=February 16, 2020}}</ref> In another news, Aguilar ended liking the character as well as his fellow companions, wishing to find merchandising of Tanjiro.<ref>{{cite tweet |author=Zach Aguilar|user=airzach\n|number=1226362613019234306 |date=February 9, 2020 |title=It\u2019s been such an honor being a part of this incredibly talented cast! Thank you @mummynyan!! I\u2019m going to find a way to bring home a Tanjiro plush no matter what it takes|access-date=February 17, 2020}}</ref> Allegra Clark voices Tanjiro as an infant.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/simplyallegra/status/1236577330023165953?s=21|title=Okay, yes, that was definitely still me as babby Tanjiro!!! (wooooooo) Also the end of the episode made me tear up. I don't even have words except to say: WOW, that was powerful.|last=Clark|first=Allegra|date=2020-03-08|website=@simplyallegra|language=en|access-date=2020-03-10}}</ref>\n\n==Appearances==\nThe main protagonist, Tanjiro Kamado is the oldest son of a charcoal-seller. His entire family was massacred by Muzan Kibutsuji while he was selling charcoal, with only his sister Nezuko surviving. His goal is to find a cure for her and turn her back into a human, and it is to this end that he decides to join the Demon Slayer Corps.<ref>{{cite book|title=Demon Slayer: Kimetsu no Yaiba|isbn=978-1-9747-0052-3|volume=1|chapter=1|publisher=Viz Media|year=2018|author=Got\u014dge, Koyoharu}}</ref> He initially trains under Sakonji Urokodaki, learning the {{Nihongo|\"Water Breathing\"|\u6c34\u306e\u547c\u5438\u6cd5|Mizu no Koky\u016b-h\u014d}} sword-style,<ref>{{cite book|title=Demon Slayer: Kimetsu no Yaiba|isbn=978-1-9747-0052-3|volume=1|chapter=4|publisher=Viz Media|year=2018|author=Got\u014dge, Koyoharu}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|title=Demon Slayer: Kimetsu no Yaiba|isbn=978-1-9747-0052-3|volume=1|chapter=7|publisher=Viz Media|year=2018|author=Got\u014dge, Koyoharu}}</ref> but later in his battle with Rui he began to use his family's {{Nihongo|Hinokami [[Kagura]]|\u30d2\u30ce\u30ab\u30df\u795e\u697d||lit. \"Dance of the Sun God\"}} technique, which itself is based on the original breath style, the {{Nihongo|Sun Breathing|{{Ruby|\u65e5|\u3072}}\u306e{{Ruby|\u547c|\u3053}}{{Ruby|\u5438|\u304d\u3085\u3046}}|Hi no Koky\u016b}}, merging both to create a more sustainable fighting style. His skull is extremely thick and his headbutts are often used as gags throughout the series. He is a kind-hearted boy and often feels sympathy for demons and their victims. His endless optimism and simple nature often has people enjoy his company, but at the same time, it also puts him at odds with certain personalities. Tanjiro has a heightened sense of smell which allows him to track down demons and evade their attacks. His sword's color is black, occasionally turning crimson red and becoming much stronger when combined with Nezuko's Blood Burst, a technique he later learns to perform without her help.\n\nA [[light novel]] entitled ''Demon Slayer: Flower of Happiness'' chronicles the lives of Tanjiro and Zenitsu before the start of the main series.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://kimetsu.com/news/?id=49766|script-title=ja:\u300c\u9b3c\u6ec5\u306e\u5203\u300d\u516c\u5f0f\u30dd\u30fc\u30bf\u30eb\u30b5\u30a4\u30c8|website=kimetsu.com|url-status=live|access-date=2019-10-06}}</ref> Merchandising based on Tanjiro has also been released.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.otakuusamagazine.com/posable-demon-slayer-kimetsu-no-yaiba-figure-can/|title=Posable Demon Slayer: Kimetsu no Yaiba Figure Can Do It All|website=Otaku USA|access-date=February 16, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.otakuusamagazine.com/sony-demon-slayer-yaiba-walkman/|title=Sony Releases Demon Slayer: Kimetsu no Yaiba Walkman, Headphones|website=Otaku USA|access-date=February 24, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Reception==\n===Critical===\nCritical reception to Tanjiro's character has been positive ever since his introduction. ''[[Otaku USA]]'' found Tanjiro an anti-stereotypical take from the shonen main characters due to his desire to fight being solely to find a cure to protect Nezuko, calling him as a \"fascinating breath of fresh air\", while highlighting his friendly personality in a dark story.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.otakuusamagazine.com/demon-slayer-kimetsu-no-yaiba-anime-review/|title=Demon Slayer: Kimetsu no Yaiba is a breath of fresh air to the shonen genre|website=Otaku USA|access-date=February 16, 2020}}</ref> Anime News Network also liked Tanjiro's design due to how it translates the narrative of his family being poor, while also liking the way the characters lives with them and later only Nezuko.<ref>{{cite web|title=Demon Slayer: Kimetsu no Yaiba|website=Anime News Network|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/review/demon-slayer/kimetsu-no-yaiba/gn-1/.134454|accessdate=February 16, 2020}}</ref> Comic Book Bin felt Tanjiro's journey was inspirational due the pain he goes to save Nezuko, making him likable.<ref>{{cite web|title=Demon Slayer: Kimetsu No Yaiba Volume 1 manga review|website=Comic Book Bin|url=http://www.comicbookbin.com/demonslayer001.html|accessdate=April 15, 2020}}</ref> While noting that the character becomes a warrior in the second manga volume, the writer believed he might experience major pain through his quest.<ref>{{cite web|title=Demon Slayer: Kimetsu No Yaiba Volume 2 manga review|website=Comic Book Bin|url=http://www.comicbookbin.com/demonslayer002.html|accessdate=April 15, 2020}}</ref> Nevertheless, regardless of how many battles he takes, Comic Book Bin enjoyed how Tanjiro retained his caring personality.<ref>{{cite web|title=Demon Slayer: Kimetsu No Yaiba Volume 3 manga review|website=Comic Book Bin|url=http://www.comicbookbin.com/demonslayer003.html|accessdate=April 15, 2020}}</ref> [[IGN]] noted that despite similarities between ''Kimetsu no Yaiba'' and other series from the same genre, Tanjiro also stands out due to his caring traits, comparing him to [[Allen Walker]] from [[Katsura Hoshino]]'s ''[[D.Gray-man]]'' series who also exhibits these traits when being faced with the dilemma of hurting an enemy. Tanjiro's relationship with Nezuko was acclaimed by IGN as \"one of the most endearing parts of ''Demon Slayer'', if not arguably its beating heart and soul\".<ref>{{cite web|title=Ufotable's Demon Slayer: Kimetsu no Yaiba Stirs Up the Shonen Anime Formula\n|url=https://www.ign.com/articles/2019/08/08/ufotables-demon-slayer-kimetsu-no-yaiba-stirs-up-the-shonen-anime-formula |website=IGN|accessdate=February 16, 2020}}</ref> Fandom Post also liked Tanjiro's care for others even if the other characters he meets are antagonists, with most of them being demons. As a result, Fandom Post believed the writing in the manga made him endearing.<ref>{{cite web|title=Demon Slayer: Kimetsu no Yaiba Vol. #03 Manga Review|url=https://www.fandompost.com/2019/11/28/demon-slayer-kimetsu-no-yaiba-vol-03-manga-review/ |website=Fandom Post|accessdate=February 16, 2020|date=2019-11-28 }}</ref> Similarly, Manga.Tokyo questioned how would Tanjiro change in his quest due to his need of becoming stronger and whether or not he might reach the happy ending he wants.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://manga.tokyo/anime-review/demon-slayer-kimetsu-no-yaiba-episode-23-review-hashira-meeting/|title=Demon Slayer: Kimetsu no Yaiba Episode 23 Review: Hashira Meeting|website=Manga.Tokyo|accessdate=April 15, 2020}}</ref>\n\nIn regards to Ufotable's handling of the series, Manga.Tokyo liked his visual appearance, finding it outstanding within the ''shonen'' genre, but felt that his struggle with Giyu was harsh, making the main character more likable. [[Natsuki Hanae]]'s performance as Tanjiro's Japanese voice actor was praised by the reviewer.<ref>{{cite web|title=Demon Slayer: Kimetsu no Yaiba Episode 1 Review: Cruelty\n|url=https://manga.tokyo/anime-review/demon-slayer-kimetsu-no-yaiba-episode-1-review-cruelty/ |website=Fandom Post|accessdate=February 16, 2020|date=2019-04-08 }}</ref> [[Anime News Network]] shared similar feelings, but felt that his traits made him predictable.<ref>{{cite web|title=Demon Slayer: Kimetsu no Yaiba\n|website=Anime News Network|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/preview-guide/2019/spring/demon-slayer-kimetsu-no-yaiba/.145459}}</ref> Nevertheless, the handling of Tanjiro's horror in regards to Nezuko's condition was the subject of praise.<ref>{{cite web|title=Demon Slayer: Kimetsu no Yaiba\n|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/review/demon-slayer-kimetsu-no-yaiba/episodes-1-2/.145722 |website=Anime News Network|accessdate=February 16, 2020}}</ref> The Fandom Post enjoyed Tanjiro's debut in the series due to how Ufotable handled the character's shock upon the tragedy of his family and how he battles Giyu in order to protect his sister. As a result, he sees Tanjiro as a character with potential to be appealing.<ref>{{cite web|title=Demon Slayer: Kimetsu no Yaiba Episode #01 Anime Review\n|url=https://www.fandompost.com/2019/04/08/demon-slayer-kimetsu-no-yaiba-episode-01-anime-review/|website=The Fandom Post|accessdate=February 16, 2020|date=2019-04-08}}</ref> The Fandom Post enjoyed how skilled Tanjiro became in the manga's tenth volume, making it one of the best reasons to keep following the printed media.<ref>{{cite web|title=Demon Slayer Vol. #10 Manga Review|url=https://www.fandompost.com/2020/02/15/demon-slayer-vol-10-manga-review/|website=The Fandom Post|accessdate=April 15, 2020|date=2020-02-15}}</ref> \n\nWriting for [[Comic Book Resources]], Sage Ashford praised the protagonists, whom he called \"the most likable male and female leads of the decade\".<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.cbr.com/anime-best-series-last-decade-ranked/ | title=10 Best Anime Series of the Last Decade, Ranked | first=Sage | last=Ashford | date=November 27, 2019 | website=Comic Book Resources | access-date=December 3, 2019}}</ref> ''Gadget Ts\u016bshin'' listed both the breathing techniques suffix and \"Ah! The era, the era changed again!\" in their 2019 anime buzzwords list.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/interest/2019-12-04/demon-slayer-dr-stone-zombie-land-saga-buzzwords-make-gadget-tsushin-2019-list/.153903|title=Demon Slayer, Dr. Stone, Zombie Land Saga Buzzwords Make Gadget Ts\u016bshin 2019 List|work=[[Anime News Network]]|first1=Lynzee|last1=Loveridge|first2=Kim|last2=Morrissy|date=December 4, 2019|accessdate=December 14, 2019}}</ref> Manga.Tokyo felt Tanjiro's characterization to be unique within the series the writer has seen, citing the scenes where the character cheers himself up and tries to work for his responsibilities.<ref>{{cite web|title=The Strong Points of Shonen Jump Manga Kimetsu no Yaiba|url=https://manga.tokyo/otaku-articles/the-charms-of-shonen-jump-manga-kimetsu-no-yaiba/2/ |website=Manga.Tokyo|accessdate=February 16, 2020|date=2017-09-03 }}</ref> Tanjiro's skills in regards to his breathing was noted to be one of most surprising events in the anime series by Latin America's IGN.<ref>{{cite web|title=Kimetsu no Yaiba: las 7 revelaciones m\u00e1s impactantes de la serie|url=https://latam.ign.com/kimetsu-no-yaiba/65211/news/kimetsu-no-yaiba-las-7-revelaciones-mas-impactantes-de-la-serie |website=IGN|accessdate=February 16, 2020|language=Spanish|date=2019-11-29 }}</ref>\n\n===Popularity===\nTanjiro's character has been popular. He was ranked in 1st place as of the first ''Demon Slayer'' character popularity poll with 6,742 votes.<ref>{{cite web |title=\u3010\u9b3c\u6ec5\u306e\u5203\u3011\u7b2c\uff11\u56de\u4eba\u6c17\u6295\u7968\u7d50\u679c\uff01\uff01\u6c17\u306b\u306a\u308b\u70ad\u6cbb\u90ce\u3001\u5584\u9038\u3001\u7149\u7344\u3055\u3093\u306e\u9806\u4f4d\u306f\uff1f|url=https://jump-archive.net/matome/ranking/kimetu/ |website=Jump Archive|language=Japanese |accessdate=February 17, 2020}}</ref> In February 2020 at [[Crunchyroll Anime Awards]], Tanjiro won the \"Best Boy\" category and the fight of Tanjiro and his sister Nezuko against Rui won the \"Best Fight Scene\" category.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Loveridge |first1=Lynzee |title=Demon Slayer: Kimetsu no Yaiba Takes Home Anime of the Year at Crunchyroll's Anime Awards |url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/interest/2020-02-15/demon-slayer-kimetsu-no-yaiba-takes-home-anime-of-the-year-at-crunchyroll-anime-awards/.156482 |website=[[Anime News Network]] |accessdate=February 16, 2020 |date=February 15, 2020}}</ref> He won the ''[[Newtype]]'' \"best male character\" award for his role in the series, along with Natsuki Hanae also being awarded for his performance as Tanjiro.<ref>{{cite web |title=Demon Slayer: Kimetsu no Yaiba, Promare Anime Win Top Newtype Anime Awards |url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-10-27/demon-slayer-kimetsu-no-yaiba-promare-anime-win-top-newtype-anime-awards/.152678 |website=[[Anime News Network]] |accessdate=27 October 2019}}</ref> According to Comic Book Resources, Tanjiro's hanafuda earring are also highly popular within the fanbase.<ref>{{cite web |title=Demon Slayer: 10 Historical Connections To Actual Japanese History You Never Noticed |url=https://www.cbr.com/demon-slayer-unknown-trivia-facts-historical-connections-to-japanese-history/ |website=[[Comic Book Resources]] |accessdate=February 17, 2020 |date=February 15, 2020}}</ref> The same site also made a list of the 10 best quotes the character says in the anime series.<ref>{{cite web |title=10 Best Quotes Said By Tanjiro In Demon Slayer|url=https://www.cbr.com/10-best-quotes-said-by-tanjiro-in-demon-slayer/ |website=[[Comic Book Resources]] |accessdate=February 17, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Demon Slayer: Kimetsu no Yaiba}}\n\n[[Category:Comics characters introduced in 2016]]\n[[Category:Male characters in anime and manga]]\n[[Category:Orphan characters in anime and manga]]\n[[Category:Teenage characters in anime and manga]]\n[[Category:Fictional swordsmen]]\n[[Category:Fictional Japanese people in anime and manga]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox animanga character\n| name         = Tanjiro Kamado\n| series       = [[Demon Slayer: Kimetsu no Yaiba]]\n| creator      = Koyoharu Got\u014dge\n| image        = Tanjirou_manga.png\n| caption      = The original manga illustration of Tanjiro preparing to draw his sword.\n| first        = ''Demon Slayer: Kimetsu no Yaiba'' chapter 1: Cruelty (2016)\n| relatives    = Tanjuro Kamado (father, deceased) <br> Kie Kamado (mother, deceased) <br> [[List of Demon Slayer: Kimetsu no Yaiba characters#Nezuko Kamado|Nezuko Kamado]] (sister) <br> Takeo Kamado (brother, deceased) <br> Hanako Kamado (sister, deceased) <br> Shigeru Kamado (brother, deceased) <br> Rokuta Kamado (brother, deceased)\n| voiced by = [[Natsuki Hanae]], [[Satomi Sat\u014d]] (child)<ref name=\"stars\">{{cite web |url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2018-10-05/demon-slayer-kimetsu-no-yaiba-anime-stars-natsuki-hanae-akari-kito/.137769 |title=Demon Slayer: Kimetsu no Yaiba Anime Stars Natsuki Hanae, Akari Kit\u014d |last=Pineda |first=Rafael Antonio |date=October 5, 2018 |website=[[Anime News Network]] |accessdate=October 5, 2018 }}</ref><br/>Zach Aguilar,<ref name=\"English1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-10-09/demon-slayer-kimetsu-no-yaiba-anime-trailer-reveals-english-dub-cast/.152061|title=Demon Slayer: Kimetsu no Yaiba Anime's Trailer Reveals English Dub Cast|website=Anime News Network|access-date=2019-10-09}}</ref> Allegra Clark (child)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/simplyallegra/status/1236577330023165953?s=21|title=Okay, yes, that was definitely still me as babby Tanjiro!!! (wooooooo) Also the end of the episode made me tear up. I don't even have words except to say: WOW, that was powerful.|last=Clark|first=Allegra|date=2020-03-08|website=@simplyallegra|language=en|access-date=2020-03-10}}</ref> (English)                                                                                         \n}}\n{{Nihongo|'''Tanjiro Kamado'''|\u7ac8\u9580 \u70ad\u6cbb\u90ce|Kamado Tanjir\u014d|lead=yes}} is a fictional character in Koyoharu Got\u014dge's [[manga]] ''[[Demon Slayer: Kimetsu no Yaiba]]''. Tanjiro is a teenager who goes on a quest to restore the humanity of his sister, [[Nezuko Kamado|Nezuko]], who was turned into a demon after his family was killed by Muzan Kibutsuji. After an encounter with [[Giyu Tomioka]], a demon slayer, Tanjiro is recruited by Giyu to also become a demon slayer to help his sister turn human again and avenge his family. Besides the ''Demon Slayer: Kimetsu no Yaiba'' [[anime]] adaptation, Tanjiro has also appeared in a [[light novel]] that acts as a prequel to the manga.\n \nKoyoharu Got\u014dge created Tanjiro following a suggestion from his editor of having a bright main character who would stand out in his dark narrative. His design influenced by [[Himura Kenshin]] from [[Nobuhiro Watsuki]]'s manga ''[[Rurouni Kenshin]]'' when deciding how andrognynous the character should look. In the anime series, Tanjiro is voiced by [[Natsuki Hanae]] in Japanese and Zach Aguilar in English. The character has been well received by manga and anime critics due to his caring nature and relationship with his sister, winning multiple awards based on his popularity.\n\n==Creation and design==\n[[File:NezukoTanjiroearlysketch.jpg|thumb|left|Early sketches of Nezuko and Tanjiro]]\nTanjiro Kamado originates from Koyoharu Got\u014dge's ideas involving a one-shot with Japanese motifs. Tatsuhiko Katayama, his editor, was worried about the one-shot being too dark for the young demographic and asked Got\u014dge if he could write another type of main character who would be \"brighter\".<ref name=\"creation\">{{cite web|url=https://mangaplus.shueisha.co.jp/web_pages/234/|title=The birth of \"Demon Slayer: Kimetsu no Yaiba\"|publisher=Shueisha|website=Manga Plus|accessdate=February 16, 2020}}</ref> Got\u014dge has cited issues in the making of the character due to the contrast he has with the dark narrative. For the release of the manga's seventh chapter, Got\u014dge drew a cover of Tanjiro wielding his sword while smiling. However, due to the constrating aesthetics the manga had. As a result, Got\u014dge discarded the drawing and instead drew a similar design with Tanjiro having a serious expression.<ref>{{cite book|title=Demon Slayer: Kimetsu no Yaiba|volume=2|publisher=Viz Media|isbn=978-1-9747-0053-0|year=2018|author=Got\u014dge, Koyoharu}}</ref>\n\nIn the initial design, Tanjiro did not have a scar or wear earrings, but in the end they felt these features really accentuated the character. In the making of the cast, Tanjiro had four supporting characters who would balance each other due to their different skills. The editor commented about Tanjiro, \"[He] is a type of male main character that you don't really see much. He's so kind. He has Nezuko, so he's coming from this position where he can't just say all demons are absolute evil. He's in the gray zone.\" Tanjiro's design was also influenced by Got\u014dge's editor: He suggested giving Tanjiro a facial scar in his forehead inspired by [[Himura Kenshin]] from [[Nobuhiro Watsuki]]'s manga ''[[Rurouni Kenshin]]'' while also giving him earrings in order to balance how androgynous he would look.<ref name=\"creation\"/>\n\nYuma Takahashi, the producer behind the adaptation of the manga said he enjoyed Tanjiro's role in the manga, making him engaged in reading the series. For how Tanjiro's Water Breathing was portrayed, [[Ufotable]] received inspiration from [[Katsushika Hokusai]]'s [[ukiyo-e]] style. The first fight scene between Tanjiro and Giyu was also carefully animated to give viewers an appealing choreography.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.crunchyroll.com/es-es/anime-feature/2019/08/16/yuma-takahashi-talks-about-producing-one-of-animes-biggest-hits?referrer=community_cr_twitter_news|title=Yuma Takahashi Talks About Producing One of Anime's Biggest Hits!|publisher=Crunchyroll|accessdate=February 16, 2020}}</ref> Tanjiro's water-based techniques were created using a mix between hand-drawn animation and CGI, while his battle against Rui was one of the most worked scenes in the making. Takahashi also said that Tanjiro is his most relatable character from the series due to how his constant hard work inspires him.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/feature/2019-08-28/interview-demon-slayer-producer-yuma-takahashi/.149177|title=Interview: Demon Slayer producer Yuma Takahashi|publisher=Anime News Network|accessdate=February 16, 2020}}</ref>\n\nWhen the anime series premiered in China, Tanjiro's design was sightly altered. Due to his piercings having Rising Sun style elements, it was feared it would offend the Mainland leading to brief retouches to them.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://kotaku.com/anime-demon-slayer-kimetsu-no-yaiba-changed-slightly-a-1833879190|title=Anime Demon Slayer: Kimetsu no Yaiba Changed Slightly In China As Not To Offend|publisher=Kotaku|accessdate=February 16, 2020}}</ref>\n\n=== Voice actors ===\nTanjiro has been voiced by [[Natsuki Hanae]] in Japanese. Hanae noted that multiple response to his career involved him portraying sad characters. However, in Tanjiro's case, he said Tanjiro is on the easy side because he says what he thinks, and is not the type that thinks one way and other things. Nezuko's actress, [[Akari Kit\u014d]], said Hanae is like a big brother to her at the studio, supportive and if there are parts she has difficulty recording, Hanae would stay and wait till she finishes even though his part has finished. Hanae said she also thinks of Kit\u014d as a younger sister. He also says it is easier for him to do his best when he is around people who he is friendly with.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://natalie.mu/comic/pp/kimetsu|title=\u300c\u9b3c\u6ec5\u306e\u5203\u300d\u3068\u306f\uff1f|publisher=Ntalie|accessdate=February 16, 2020}}</ref>\n\nEnglish voice actor Zach Aguilar was overjoyed when being given the role of voicing Tanjiro in the dub due to him being a fan of the series, as well as noting he was supported by multiple fans.<ref>{{cite tweet |author=Zach Aguilar|user=airzach\n|number=1182014282487042048 |date=October 9, 2019 |title=Incredibly honored by this - I\u2019m voicing Tanjiro for the English dub of Demon Slayer! Being a huge fan of the show, I\u2019m so excited to have been able to work on this with the team at @aniplexUSA and @BangZoom. Thank you to everyone for your support!|access-date=February 16, 2020}}</ref> In another news, Aguilar ended liking the character as well as his fellow companions, wishing to find merchandising of Tanjiro.<ref>{{cite tweet |author=Zach Aguilar|user=airzach\n|number=1226362613019234306 |date=February 9, 2020 |title=It\u2019s been such an honor being a part of this incredibly talented cast! Thank you @mummynyan!! I\u2019m going to find a way to bring home a Tanjiro plush no matter what it takes|access-date=February 17, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Appearances==\nThe main protagonist, Tanjiro Kamado is the oldest son of a charcoal-seller. His entire family was massacred by Muzan Kibutsuji while he was selling charcoal, with only his sister Nezuko surviving. His goal is to find a cure for her and turn her back into a human, and it is to this end that he decides to join the Demon Slayer Corps.<ref>{{cite book|title=Demon Slayer: Kimetsu no Yaiba|isbn=978-1-9747-0052-3|volume=1|chapter=1|publisher=Viz Media|year=2018|author=Got\u014dge, Koyoharu}}</ref> He initially trains under Sakonji Urokodaki, learning the {{Nihongo|\"Water Breathing\"|\u6c34\u306e\u547c\u5438\u6cd5|Mizu no Koky\u016b-h\u014d}} sword-style,<ref>{{cite book|title=Demon Slayer: Kimetsu no Yaiba|isbn=978-1-9747-0052-3|volume=1|chapter=4|publisher=Viz Media|year=2018|author=Got\u014dge, Koyoharu}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|title=Demon Slayer: Kimetsu no Yaiba|isbn=978-1-9747-0052-3|volume=1|chapter=7|publisher=Viz Media|year=2018|author=Got\u014dge, Koyoharu}}</ref> but later in his battle with Rui he began to use his family's {{Nihongo|Hinokami [[Kagura]]|\u30d2\u30ce\u30ab\u30df\u795e\u697d||lit. \"Dance of the Sun God\"}} technique, which itself is based on the original breath style, the {{Nihongo|Sun Breathing|{{Ruby|\u65e5|\u3072}}\u306e{{Ruby|\u547c|\u3053}}{{Ruby|\u5438|\u304d\u3085\u3046}}|Hi no Koky\u016b}}, merging both to create a more sustainable fighting style. His skull is extremely thick and his headbutts are often used as gags throughout the series. He is a kind-hearted boy and often feels sympathy for demons and their victims. His endless optimism and simple nature often has people enjoy his company, but at the same time, it also puts him at odds with certain personalities. Tanjiro has a heightened sense of smell which allows him to track down demons and evade their attacks. His sword's color is black, occasionally turning crimson red and becoming much stronger when combined with Nezuko's Blood Burst, a technique he later learns to perform without her help.\n\nA [[light novel]] entitled ''Demon Slayer: Flower of Happiness'' chronicles the lives of Tanjiro and Zenitsu before the start of the main series.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://kimetsu.com/news/?id=49766|script-title=ja:\u300c\u9b3c\u6ec5\u306e\u5203\u300d\u516c\u5f0f\u30dd\u30fc\u30bf\u30eb\u30b5\u30a4\u30c8|website=kimetsu.com|url-status=live|access-date=2019-10-06}}</ref> Merchandising based on Tanjiro has also been released.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.otakuusamagazine.com/posable-demon-slayer-kimetsu-no-yaiba-figure-can/|title=Posable Demon Slayer: Kimetsu no Yaiba Figure Can Do It All|website=Otaku USA|access-date=February 16, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.otakuusamagazine.com/sony-demon-slayer-yaiba-walkman/|title=Sony Releases Demon Slayer: Kimetsu no Yaiba Walkman, Headphones|website=Otaku USA|access-date=February 24, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Reception==\n===Critical===\nCritical reception to Tanjiro's character has been positive ever since his introduction. ''[[Otaku USA]]'' found Tanjiro an anti-stereotypical take from the shonen main characters due to his desire to fight being solely to find a cure to protect Nezuko, calling him as a \"fascinating breath of fresh air\", while highlighting his friendly personality in a dark story.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.otakuusamagazine.com/demon-slayer-kimetsu-no-yaiba-anime-review/|title=Demon Slayer: Kimetsu no Yaiba is a breath of fresh air to the shonen genre|website=Otaku USA|access-date=February 16, 2020}}</ref> Anime News Network also liked Tanjiro's design due to how it translates the narrative of his family being poor, while also liking the way the characters lives with them and later only Nezuko.<ref>{{cite web|title=Demon Slayer: Kimetsu no Yaiba|website=Anime News Network|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/review/demon-slayer/kimetsu-no-yaiba/gn-1/.134454|accessdate=February 16, 2020}}</ref> Comic Book Bin felt Tanjiro's journey was inspirational due the pain he goes to save Nezuko, making him likable.<ref>{{cite web|title=Demon Slayer: Kimetsu No Yaiba Volume 1 manga review|website=Comic Book Bin|url=http://www.comicbookbin.com/demonslayer001.html|accessdate=April 15, 2020}}</ref> While noting that the character becomes a warrior in the second manga volume, the writer believed he might experience major pain through his quest.<ref>{{cite web|title=Demon Slayer: Kimetsu No Yaiba Volume 2 manga review|website=Comic Book Bin|url=http://www.comicbookbin.com/demonslayer002.html|accessdate=April 15, 2020}}</ref> Nevertheless, regardless of how many battles he takes, Comic Book Bin enjoyed how Tanjiro retained his caring personality.<ref>{{cite web|title=Demon Slayer: Kimetsu No Yaiba Volume 3 manga review|website=Comic Book Bin|url=http://www.comicbookbin.com/demonslayer003.html|accessdate=April 15, 2020}}</ref> [[IGN]] noted that despite similarities between ''Kimetsu no Yaiba'' and other series from the same genre, Tanjiro also stands out due to his caring traits, comparing him to [[Allen Walker]] from [[Katsura Hoshino]]'s ''[[D.Gray-man]]'' series who also exhibits these traits when being faced with the dilemma of hurting an enemy. Tanjiro's relationship with Nezuko was acclaimed by IGN as \"one of the most endearing parts of ''Demon Slayer'', if not arguably its beating heart and soul\".<ref>{{cite web|title=Ufotable's Demon Slayer: Kimetsu no Yaiba Stirs Up the Shonen Anime Formula\n|url=https://www.ign.com/articles/2019/08/08/ufotables-demon-slayer-kimetsu-no-yaiba-stirs-up-the-shonen-anime-formula |website=IGN|accessdate=February 16, 2020}}</ref> Fandom Post also liked Tanjiro's care for others even if the other characters he meets are antagonists, with most of them being demons. As a result, Fandom Post believed the writing in the manga made him endearing.<ref>{{cite web|title=Demon Slayer: Kimetsu no Yaiba Vol. #03 Manga Review|url=https://www.fandompost.com/2019/11/28/demon-slayer-kimetsu-no-yaiba-vol-03-manga-review/ |website=Fandom Post|accessdate=February 16, 2020|date=2019-11-28 }}</ref> Similarly, Manga.Tokyo questioned how would Tanjiro change in his quest due to his need of becoming stronger and whether or not he might reach the happy ending he wants.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://manga.tokyo/anime-review/demon-slayer-kimetsu-no-yaiba-episode-23-review-hashira-meeting/|title=Demon Slayer: Kimetsu no Yaiba Episode 23 Review: Hashira Meeting|website=Manga.Tokyo|accessdate=April 15, 2020}}</ref>\n\nIn regards to Ufotable's handling of the series, Manga.Tokyo liked his visual appearance, finding it outstanding within the ''shonen'' genre, but felt that his struggle with Giyu was harsh, making the main character more likable. [[Natsuki Hanae]]'s performance as Tanjiro's Japanese voice actor was praised by the reviewer.<ref>{{cite web|title=Demon Slayer: Kimetsu no Yaiba Episode 1 Review: Cruelty\n|url=https://manga.tokyo/anime-review/demon-slayer-kimetsu-no-yaiba-episode-1-review-cruelty/ |website=Fandom Post|accessdate=February 16, 2020|date=2019-04-08 }}</ref> [[Anime News Network]] shared similar feelings, but felt that his traits made him predictable.<ref>{{cite web|title=Demon Slayer: Kimetsu no Yaiba\n|website=Anime News Network|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/preview-guide/2019/spring/demon-slayer-kimetsu-no-yaiba/.145459}}</ref> Nevertheless, the handling of Tanjiro's horror in regards to Nezuko's condition was the subject of praise.<ref>{{cite web|title=Demon Slayer: Kimetsu no Yaiba\n|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/review/demon-slayer-kimetsu-no-yaiba/episodes-1-2/.145722 |website=Anime News Network|accessdate=February 16, 2020}}</ref> The Fandom Post enjoyed Tanjiro's debut in the series due to how Ufotable handled the character's shock upon the tragedy of his family and how he battles Giyu in order to protect his sister. As a result, he sees Tanjiro as a character with potential to be appealing.<ref>{{cite web|title=Demon Slayer: Kimetsu no Yaiba Episode #01 Anime Review\n|url=https://www.fandompost.com/2019/04/08/demon-slayer-kimetsu-no-yaiba-episode-01-anime-review/|website=The Fandom Post|accessdate=February 16, 2020|date=2019-04-08}}</ref> The Fandom Post enjoyed how skilled Tanjiro became in the manga's tenth volume, making it one of the best reasons to keep following the printed media.<ref>{{cite web|title=Demon Slayer Vol. #10 Manga Review|url=https://www.fandompost.com/2020/02/15/demon-slayer-vol-10-manga-review/|website=The Fandom Post|accessdate=April 15, 2020|date=2020-02-15}}</ref> \n\nWriting for [[Comic Book Resources]], Sage Ashford praised the protagonists, whom he called \"the most likable male and female leads of the decade\".<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.cbr.com/anime-best-series-last-decade-ranked/ | title=10 Best Anime Series of the Last Decade, Ranked | first=Sage | last=Ashford | date=November 27, 2019 | website=Comic Book Resources | access-date=December 3, 2019}}</ref> ''Gadget Ts\u016bshin'' listed both the breathing techniques suffix and \"Ah! The era, the era changed again!\" in their 2019 anime buzzwords list.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/interest/2019-12-04/demon-slayer-dr-stone-zombie-land-saga-buzzwords-make-gadget-tsushin-2019-list/.153903|title=Demon Slayer, Dr. Stone, Zombie Land Saga Buzzwords Make Gadget Ts\u016bshin 2019 List|work=[[Anime News Network]]|first1=Lynzee|last1=Loveridge|first2=Kim|last2=Morrissy|date=December 4, 2019|accessdate=December 14, 2019}}</ref> Manga.Tokyo felt Tanjiro's characterization to be unique within the series the writer has seen, citing the scenes where the character cheers himself up and tries to work for his responsibilities.<ref>{{cite web|title=The Strong Points of Shonen Jump Manga Kimetsu no Yaiba|url=https://manga.tokyo/otaku-articles/the-charms-of-shonen-jump-manga-kimetsu-no-yaiba/2/ |website=Manga.Tokyo|accessdate=February 16, 2020|date=2017-09-03 }}</ref> Tanjiro's skills in regards to his breathing was noted to be one of most surprising events in the anime series by Latin America's IGN.<ref>{{cite web|title=Kimetsu no Yaiba: las 7 revelaciones m\u00e1s impactantes de la serie|url=https://latam.ign.com/kimetsu-no-yaiba/65211/news/kimetsu-no-yaiba-las-7-revelaciones-mas-impactantes-de-la-serie |website=IGN|accessdate=February 16, 2020|language=Spanish|date=2019-11-29 }}</ref>\n\n===Popularity===\nTanjiro's character has been popular. He was ranked in 1st place as of the first ''Demon Slayer'' character popularity poll with 6,742 votes.<ref>{{cite web |title=\u3010\u9b3c\u6ec5\u306e\u5203\u3011\u7b2c\uff11\u56de\u4eba\u6c17\u6295\u7968\u7d50\u679c\uff01\uff01\u6c17\u306b\u306a\u308b\u70ad\u6cbb\u90ce\u3001\u5584\u9038\u3001\u7149\u7344\u3055\u3093\u306e\u9806\u4f4d\u306f\uff1f|url=https://jump-archive.net/matome/ranking/kimetu/ |website=Jump Archive|language=Japanese |accessdate=February 17, 2020}}</ref> In February 2020 at [[Crunchyroll Anime Awards]], Tanjiro won the \"Best Boy\" category and the fight of Tanjiro and his sister Nezuko against Rui won the \"Best Fight Scene\" category.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Loveridge |first1=Lynzee |title=Demon Slayer: Kimetsu no Yaiba Takes Home Anime of the Year at Crunchyroll's Anime Awards |url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/interest/2020-02-15/demon-slayer-kimetsu-no-yaiba-takes-home-anime-of-the-year-at-crunchyroll-anime-awards/.156482 |website=[[Anime News Network]] |accessdate=February 16, 2020 |date=February 15, 2020}}</ref> He won the ''[[Newtype]]'' \"best male character\" award for his role in the series, along with Natsuki Hanae also being awarded for his performance as Tanjiro.<ref>{{cite web |title=Demon Slayer: Kimetsu no Yaiba, Promare Anime Win Top Newtype Anime Awards |url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-10-27/demon-slayer-kimetsu-no-yaiba-promare-anime-win-top-newtype-anime-awards/.152678 |website=[[Anime News Network]] |accessdate=27 October 2019}}</ref> According to Comic Book Resources, Tanjiro's hanafuda earring are also highly popular within the fanbase.<ref>{{cite web |title=Demon Slayer: 10 Historical Connections To Actual Japanese History You Never Noticed |url=https://www.cbr.com/demon-slayer-unknown-trivia-facts-historical-connections-to-japanese-history/ |website=[[Comic Book Resources]] |accessdate=February 17, 2020 |date=February 15, 2020}}</ref> The same site also made a list of the 10 best quotes the character says in the anime series.<ref>{{cite web |title=10 Best Quotes Said By Tanjiro In Demon Slayer|url=https://www.cbr.com/10-best-quotes-said-by-tanjiro-in-demon-slayer/ |website=[[Comic Book Resources]] |accessdate=February 17, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Demon Slayer: Kimetsu no Yaiba}}\n\n[[Category:Comics characters introduced in 2016]]\n[[Category:Male characters in anime and manga]]\n[[Category:Orphan characters in anime and manga]]\n[[Category:Teenage characters in anime and manga]]\n[[Category:Fictional swordsmen]]\n[[Category:Fictional Japanese people in anime and manga]]\n", "name_user": "Tintor2", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tanjiro_Kamado"}
